Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.78,0:01:00.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,改編自真人真事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.93,0:01:02.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,February 1993.\N{\rCHT}1993年2月{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.92,0:01:04.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,A massive explosion\N{\rCHT}劇烈爆炸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.22,0:01:06.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,ripping through the lower basement sections.\N{\rCHT}炸穿了世貿中心{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.84,0:01:09.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,of the World Trade Center under tower number two.\N{\rCHT}2號樓的地下樓層{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.46,0:01:12.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,A terrorist bomb, how horrific a crime this is.\N{\rCHT}這是一枚恐攻炸彈 真是罪大惡極{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.56,0:01:14.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,August 1998.\N{\rCHT}1998年8月{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.62,0:01:18.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Our embassies in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam were bombed.\N{\rCHT}我國在奈洛比和薩拉姆港的使館 發生爆炸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.50,0:01:21.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Bin Laden terrorist network was responsible.\N{\rCHT}幕後主使 為本·拉登的恐怖分子網路{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.48,0:01:23.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Suicide bombers blew a hole in the ship.\N{\rCHT}自殺炸彈客 將艦身炸出大洞{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:26.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,My prayers are with the families of those killed...\N{\rCHT}我衷心為科爾號爆炸案中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.09,0:01:29.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,at the explosion involving the U.S. naval vessel Cole.\N{\rCHT}不幸罹難者的家屬們祈禱{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hidden in the mountains of Afghanistan,\N{\rCHT}隱身阿富汗深山中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.73,0:01:33.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bin Laden planned these attacks.\N{\rCHT}本·拉登策劃了這些攻擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.76,0:01:35.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,September 9th, 2001.\N{\rCHT}2001年9月9日{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.79,0:01:37.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ahmad Shah Massoud,\N{\rCHT}北方聯盟領袖{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.08,0:01:38.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,the leader of the Northern Alliance,\N{\rCHT}艾哈邁德·沙阿馬·蘇德{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.69,0:01:41.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,was assassinated by two members of Al-Qaeda.\N{\rCHT}遭兩名基地組織成員刺殺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.37,0:01:44.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Massoud's death destabilized the Northern Alliance,\N{\rCHT}馬蘇德之死 讓北方聯盟失去穩定{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:47.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,removing the only threat to the Taliban's power in Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}清除了塔利班在當地的唯一威脅{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.83,0:01:50.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,普京: 我對美國同伴說
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.38,0:01:52.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我非常擔憂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.80,0:01:55.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,就要出大事了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.30,0:01:58.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們正在策劃陰謀
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.26,0:02:04.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,2001年9月11日 肯塔基州 坎貝爾堡 上午7:45
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.15,0:02:08.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't believe we have a fireplace.\N{\rCHT}這裡居然有壁爐{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.86,0:02:11.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Sort of a fireplace. It's propane.\N{\rCHT}是啊 勉強算是 那是燒瓦斯的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:12.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a fireplace.\N{\rCHT}它就是壁爐{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.81,0:02:14.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maddy?\N{\rCHT}瑪蒂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.50,0:02:20.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Up you go.\N{\rCHT}來 過來坐好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.59,0:02:22.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}來吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.00,0:02:24.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's get your shoes on.\N{\rCHT}來穿鞋子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:26.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, I like your drawings.\N{\rCHT}我喜歡你的畫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.45,0:02:27.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a ladybug.\N{\rCHT}那是瓢蟲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:29.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,A ladybug? Wow, it's beautiful.\N{\rCHT}瓢蟲啊 好漂亮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:33.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna unpack this room until we get the walls painted.\N{\rCHT}我想等我們粉刷完 再整理東西{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.69,0:02:35.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,And by "we", I mean you.\N{\rCHT}我說的"我們"是指你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.73,0:02:37.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a lot of work.\N{\rCHT}聽起來會很累{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.91,0:02:40.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what does that mean?\N{\rCHT}什麼意思{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.14,0:02:41.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Paint the walls and I'll show you.\N{\rCHT}你乖乖粉刷就知道了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.57,0:02:44.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,I love this house.\N{\rCHT}我愛這棟房子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.27,0:02:47.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gotta learn Spanish, Daddy.\N{\rCHT}爸爸 你要學西班牙語啦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:49.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's on the list, sweetie.\N{\rCHT}已經列入待辦清單了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:51.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You taking me to school again?\N{\rCHT}你又要送我去上學嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.20,0:02:52.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. And picking you up.\N{\rCHT}我還會去接你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.59,0:02:54.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Really? - Yeah!\N{\rCHT}- 真的嗎 - 是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:56.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Turn that down, sweetie.\N{\rCHT}把聲音關小{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.19,0:03:01.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Daddy, look.\N{\rCHT}爸爸 你看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:06.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Two planes have crashed into the World Trade Center\N{\rCHT}兩架飛機撞進世貿中心{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.09,0:03:09.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,in an apparent terrorist attack on the country.\N{\rCHT}這顯然是對我國的恐攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.42,0:03:11.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have reported that one of the planes\N{\rCHT}先前報導其中一架{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:14.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,was an American Airlines 767\N{\rCHT}是美航波音767{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.12,0:03:15.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,that had been hijacked...\N{\rCHT}該飛機遭劫持{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.42,0:03:23.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,肯塔基州 坎伯蘭河 撤出演習 上午8:31
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.41,0:03:38.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey! - Thank God! Finally.\N{\rCHT}- 嗨 - 總算來了啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.68,0:03:39.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay!\N{\rCHT}好了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.33,0:03:45.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Really?\N{\rCHT}真的假的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.05,0:03:46.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Really?\N{\rCHT}當真{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.40,0:03:51.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What the hell, man? - Relax, bro.\N{\rCHT}- 你搞什麼啊 - 別激動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.26,0:03:52.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You know how nuts traffic is right now. - Traffic?\N{\rCHT}- 你也知道現在有多堵 - 堵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:03:55.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We've been freezing our asses out here all goddamn night! - Relax, bro.\N{\rCHT}- 我們在這裡凍了一晚 - 別激動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:56.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you jump your ass in this river?\N{\rCHT}你去跳河看看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:03:57.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,What, did you stop at Starbucks?\N{\rCHT}你是去星巴克嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.28,0:04:00.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Where's my latte? - Milo, it's 8:30.\N{\rCHT}- 我的拿鐵呢 - 都8點半了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:01.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,What happened?\N{\rCHT}出了什麼事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:03.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What, you guys don't know? - No, we were in the river, man.\N{\rCHT}- 你們不知道嗎 - 我們泡在河裡 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.85,0:04:12.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Goddamn, they're low.\N{\rCHT}靠 飛真低{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:14.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that part of a drill?\N{\rCHT}那也是演習嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ain't no drill.\N{\rCHT}那不是演習{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:23.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get me Josh Bailey at USASOC intel, please.\N{\rCHT}請接陸軍特戰部軍情隊的貝利{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:31.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bailey on line three, sir.\N{\rCHT}長官 貝利在三線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:33.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you say line three? Sound off!\N{\rCHT}你說三線嗎 大聲點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.81,0:04:38.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Josh, Jesus Christ, you guys shit the bed on this one, huh?\N{\rCHT}喬希 媽的 你們這次真是慘歪歪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.93,0:04:40.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Was it confirmed?\N{\rCHT}有確認嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.18,0:04:43.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not my job to know where. That's your job.\N{\rCHT}搞清楚地點是你的工作{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:45.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,All we are is ready.\N{\rCHT}我們只管隨時上陣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.08,0:04:46.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, quit wasting time talking to me then.\N{\rCHT}那就別再跟我廢話{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:50.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why are you here? Out of uniform with that fur on your face.\N{\rCHT}你來幹嘛 沒穿制服還滿臉鬍子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:52.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Didn't you get back from Kuwait, like, three weeks ago?\N{\rCHT}你不是3周前從科威特回來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:54.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. Apologies. Technically, I'm still on leave.\N{\rCHT}長官抱歉 嚴格來說我還在放假{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're here today, leave is over.\N{\rCHT}既然來了 假期就結束了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.88,0:04:58.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Take a look around, Captain. We're a little busy.\N{\rCHT}你自己看看 我們有點忙{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.37,0:05:01.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What do you want? - I want back on my team, sir.\N{\rCHT}- 有什麼事 - 長官 我要歸隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:02.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't have a team.\N{\rCHT}你無隊可歸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.88,0:05:05.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,been rotated to my staff. At your request, by the way.\N{\rCHT}你已經轉調我的幕僚 而且是應你要求{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.62,0:05:06.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,That was before. All right?\N{\rCHT}而且是應你要求{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:09.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Before guys were flying fucking planes into buildings.\N{\rCHT}那是之前 在那些傢伙開飛機撞大樓之前{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.13,0:05:12.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, your warrant officer turned in his retirement papers,\N{\rCHT}你的準尉 已經申請退伍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.06,0:05:13.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,and you've been moved up.\N{\rCHT}你升幕僚{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.30,0:05:15.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,So your team doesn't exist, all right?\N{\rCHT}所以你沒有隊伍 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.59,0:05:18.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll be filtered into new ODAs when the opportunities arise.\N{\rCHT}等有機會 再讓你進新的分遣A隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:20.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I were you, I'd get back to your desk\N{\rCHT}我建議你回座位{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:22.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,and start studying intel on Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}去研究阿富汗情報{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:24.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Taliban sponsored the attack, sir?\N{\rCHT}是塔利班背後撐腰嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.52,0:05:25.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Al-Qaeda planned this attack.\N{\rCHT}主謀是基地組織{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:27.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,They have refuge in Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}他們在阿富汗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.42,0:05:29.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,But Middle East is our assigned region, sir.\N{\rCHT}中東是我們的專責區{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.28,0:05:31.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Really? I didn't know that!\N{\rCHT}是嗎 我都不知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.32,0:05:32.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here's the thing, though. You don't have a region,\N{\rCHT}不過你沒專責區{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.76,0:05:34.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,'cause you don't have a fucking team!\N{\rCHT}因為你沒有隊伍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:36.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,So get back to your goddamn desk and let me do my job!\N{\rCHT}回你的座位去 讓我做事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:38.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fuck.\N{\rCHT}媽的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.54,0:05:39.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sergeant, who's on line four?\N{\rCHT}中士 四線是誰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.01,0:05:43.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,It was not long before that tower collapsed.\N{\rCHT}不久之後北塔就坍塌了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:46.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,The loss of life so far is catastrophic,\N{\rCHT}目前的死傷非常慘重{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:49.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,estimated at 10,000.\N{\rCHT}估計有1萬人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.10,0:05:52.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,But that number could go much higher.\N{\rCHT}但有可能遠不止於此{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.34,0:05:54.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,These images from just across\N{\rCHT}這是隔著波多馬克河{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.07,0:05:56.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,the Potomac River of the Pentagon,\N{\rCHT}拍的五角大廈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:05:58.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,still on fire, a fire\N{\rCHT}大火還在失控燃燒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.89,0:06:02.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,burning out of control after a hijacked airliner, another one,\N{\rCHT}因為又一架被劫持的客機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:06.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,we believe this one to have been a United Airlines flight,\N{\rCHT}這次應該是一架聯航班機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.54,0:06:08.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,smashed into the Pentagon around 9:45..\N{\rCHT}在9點45分左右{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.69,0:06:10.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yo. What's up, Cap? - What up, Milo?\N{\rCHT}- 隊長好 - 米洛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:12.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing here? - Trying to get my team back.\N{\rCHT}- 你怎麼來了 - 我想重新整隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.42,0:06:14.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, your little jalape?o ain't gonna be too happy about that, huh?\N{\rCHT}你老婆可不會太高興吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:17.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, maybe not. - What are you talking about? This team's done.\N{\rCHT}- 應該是 - 你在說什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.61,0:06:19.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,And thanks to you, we're gonna be\N{\rCHT}隊伍解散了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.63,0:06:21.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,watching this whole thing go down on fucking CNN.\N{\rCHT}多虧你 讓我們只能看CNN盯進度{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:23.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,What I did, I did for my family.\N{\rCHT}我是為了我的家人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.21,0:06:24.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't know there was a goddamn war coming.\N{\rCHT}我又不知道會開戰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:26.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, buddy, you and your family, you're gonna be fine.\N{\rCHT}你和你家人會很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.66,0:06:27.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,From your cushy little office,\N{\rCHT}你坐辦公室{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.73,0:06:29.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,- you're gonna be fucking fine! - You think I'm gonna be sitting on the\N{\rCHT}- 幹內勤可好了 - 你以為{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:31.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,sidelines with this shit happening, Dill? Huh?\N{\rCHT}出這種事 我會袖手旁觀嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.32,0:06:33.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you talk to Bowers?\N{\rCHT}你找包爾斯談了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.78,0:06:36.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did. I told him I want back in and he said no.\N{\rCHT}談了 我說要歸隊 但他說不行{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:39.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,He won't say no to me.\N{\rCHT}他不會拒絕我的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.82,0:06:41.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me you didn't submit that paperwork.\N{\rCHT}你的請調文件還沒交吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:43.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- No, it's on my desk. - Good.\N{\rCHT}- 在我桌上 - 很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:47.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,If anybody in the Middle East did this,\N{\rCHT}如果是中東那邊的人幹的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:49.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,the Fifth Group's up.\N{\rCHT}第5特戰隊就要上了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:52.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fuck yeah, bro. Fuck yeah. I mean,\N{\rCHT}沒錯 兄弟 沒錯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:54.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,we would have been.\N{\rCHT}我們原本會上陣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:55.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we had a fucking captain.\N{\rCHT}要是我們有隊長的話{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.80,0:06:59.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll be in this fight, boys. You mark my words.\N{\rCHT}我們會上陣的 放心好了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.67,0:07:06.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's in a meeting, sir.\N{\rCHT}長官 他在開會{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.30,0:07:08.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a private meeting, sir.\N{\rCHT}是私人會議 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.58,0:07:34.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your retirement papers?\N{\rCHT}你的退伍申請書{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.48,0:07:38.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to submit, sir.\N{\rCHT}我沒有檔要遞交{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:41.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm still Chief Warrant Officer of ODA 595,\N{\rCHT}我仍然是分遣A隊595小隊的準尉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:44.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,and my team has more combat experience\N{\rCHT}我們的經驗 抵得過整個第5特戰隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:45.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,than the rest of Fifth Group combined.\N{\rCHT}我們在索馬利亞{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.55,0:07:49.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,All that hell we went through in Somalia, Desert Storm,\N{\rCHT}沙漠風暴吃的苦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.12,0:07:51.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,that means somethin'.\N{\rCHT}可不是白搭的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:54.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,You break this team up, you're cutting the head off\N{\rCHT}你拆這支隊伍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:56.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,your most venomous snake, sir.\N{\rCHT}就是自廢武功 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.34,0:07:58.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:00.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:02.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll pull you a captain and get you in the game.\N{\rCHT}我安插個隊長讓你們上陣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:03.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have a captain, sir.\N{\rCHT}我們有隊長了 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.49,0:08:05.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have a captain with no combat experience.\N{\rCHT}一個沒有作戰經驗的隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.70,0:08:07.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's never been to war.\N{\rCHT}他沒上過戰場{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.16,0:08:08.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's only led you in training.\N{\rCHT}只帶你們操練過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.78,0:08:10.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's already been bumped up to staff.\N{\rCHT}他已經升幕僚了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.39,0:08:12.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is a career wrecker. You understand that, right?\N{\rCHT}這樣是自毀前程 你明白吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:15.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, all due respect, I've spent two years\N{\rCHT}恕我直言{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.33,0:08:17.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,with that fellow leadin' our team.\N{\rCHT}我跟那傢伙相處2年{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.11,0:08:20.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you think furthering his career is why he joined,\N{\rCHT}如果你認為 他從軍是為了升官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.76,0:08:22.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,you need to get to know your captain, sir.\N{\rCHT}那你可得好好瞭解他了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.94,0:08:30.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,As you were.\N{\rCHT}不必起來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:34.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Sorry about the desk. - No, no.\N{\rCHT}- 抱歉亂踹桌子 - 沒關係{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:35.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a good kill.\N{\rCHT}踹得漂亮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:38.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Besides, you're not gonna need it where you're going.\N{\rCHT}而且你要去的地方 也用不上它{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:55.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Special Forces doesn't have thermals?\N{\rCHT}特種部隊沒有發熱衣嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:08:59.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Army wasn't expecting this.\N{\rCHT}軍中也是措手不及{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.61,0:09:00.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.78,0:09:02.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that makes two of us.\N{\rCHT}我們也是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.98,0:09:08.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,You tell him.\N{\rCHT}你跟他說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.78,0:09:10.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not doing your dirty work for you.\N{\rCHT}我可不替你當壞人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:13.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Marsha.\N{\rCHT}瑪莎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:17.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll love you when you get back.\N{\rCHT}等你回來我才會愛你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:31.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy.\N{\rCHT}嗨 小子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.70,0:09:32.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Leaving?\N{\rCHT}你要走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:35.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I gotta go.\N{\rCHT}對 不去不行{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:37.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,How long?\N{\rCHT}去多久{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.31,0:09:40.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't know.\N{\rCHT}不知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.04,0:09:46.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N{\rCHT}嘿{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:51.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know I love you, right?\N{\rCHT}你知道我愛你吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.80,0:10:10.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wow.\N{\rCHT}哇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.90,0:10:12.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Made it all the way to the oven, huh, babe?\N{\rCHT}一路刷到烤箱去了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:15.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some wives cry, I clean.\N{\rCHT}有的老婆哭 我就洗刷刷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.79,0:10:16.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey,\N{\rCHT}嘿{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.23,0:10:18.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,uh, I was thinking...\N{\rCHT}那個 我在想{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.92,0:10:20.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're gonna have all the time in the world\N{\rCHT}我走了以後{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:23.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,to clean that oven once I'm gone.\N{\rCHT}你愛刷多久就刷多久{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.38,0:10:25.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'm kind of running out of time. So...\N{\rCHT}我快要沒時間了 所以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.96,0:10:29.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I bet I know just how you wanna spend it.\N{\rCHT}我敢說 我知道你想怎麼打發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.84,0:10:30.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean,\N{\rCHT}我還有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:32.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have two hours. I'll be really quick.\N{\rCHT}2小時 我會很快的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:34.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Super quick. - Uh-huh, yeah, not a chance.\N{\rCHT}- 我超快的 - 想都別想{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:37.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Holding out is the only way I can guarantee you come back to me.\N{\rCHT}讓你憋著 才能確保你會回來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:39.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Please? - Mmm-mmm.\N{\rCHT}- 拜託啦 - 嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.61,0:10:41.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Just the tip. - Mmm-mmm.\N{\rCHT}- 一下下就好 - 嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.84,0:10:44.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Okay, you know what? - Mmm-hmm.\N{\rCHT}- 好吧 你猜怎樣 - 嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.58,0:10:46.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,War's gonna be over so quick.\N{\rCHT}戰爭很快就會結束{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.30,0:10:47.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's gonna be over in like a week.\N{\rCHT}一周就會了結{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.94,0:10:48.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,I promise.\N{\rCHT}我保證{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:52.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go wake up the kids.\N{\rCHT}把孩子叫醒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:54.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Spend the time with them.\N{\rCHT}去陪他們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.73,0:10:57.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know what I signed up for.\N{\rCHT}我知道我的處境{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.80,0:10:58.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't.\N{\rCHT}他們不知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.15,0:11:28.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't wish for what you don't want.\N{\rCHT}小心願望成真{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:35.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You were on a flight to New York two months ago.\N{\rCHT}你2個月前 也搭飛機去紐約{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:38.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't have to justify it to me.\N{\rCHT}你不必對我辯解{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:41.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a soldier's wife.\N{\rCHT}我是軍眷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.90,0:11:44.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I've been lucky.\N{\rCHT}我一直很幸運{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:47.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,All I've had to worry about so far\N{\rCHT}目前擔心過的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.61,0:11:50.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,is malaria and chopper crashes.\N{\rCHT}只有瘧疾 和直升機墜機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Most dangerous part's the ride in and out.\N{\rCHT}最危險的時候是起降{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:56.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.\N{\rCHT}已經不是了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.68,0:12:03.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't care how long you're gone\N{\rCHT}你去多久都無所謂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.87,0:12:06.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,as long as you come back.\N{\rCHT}只要回來就好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:10.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,You understand?\N{\rCHT}懂嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:12.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do.\N{\rCHT}我懂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:18.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then say you're coming home.\N{\rCHT}那就說你會回家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:22.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't, baby. It's bad luck.\N{\rCHT}不行 那樣不吉利{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:29.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need to hear you say it.\N{\rCHT}我要聽你說出口{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.23,0:12:34.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm comin' home.\N{\rCHT}我一定會回家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.99,0:12:45.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,2001年10月16日
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:48.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,烏茲別克斯坦
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.70,0:12:51.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,K2基地
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.37,0:12:54.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,阿富汗國境北方97哩
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.57,0:13:08.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, ODA 595. Where do we bunk?\N{\rCHT}分遣A隊595小隊 我們睡哪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:10.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Uh, you see those Quonset huts?\N{\rCHT}那邊的鐵皮屋{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:11.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those are for the teams.\N{\rCHT}就是營房{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:13.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,ODA numbers are on the door, sir.\N{\rCHT}門上有單位代碼 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.76,0:13:16.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't salute in country.\N{\rCHT}在敏感區不要行禮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:18.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to get our captain killed, bro?\N{\rCHT}你想害死我們隊長嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:19.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,These are all friendlies.\N{\rCHT}這些都是友軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.96,0:13:20.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?\N{\rCHT}是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:23.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who, that guy? That's not my friend.\N{\rCHT}那傢伙嗎 他可不是我朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.68,0:13:25.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,And that guy's definitely not my friend.\N{\rCHT}那傢伙絕對不是我朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.54,0:13:26.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fucking Diller, bro.\N{\rCHT}你這臭迪勒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.97,0:13:28.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I could be their friend. He looks nice.\N{\rCHT}我可以跟他交朋友 他人好像不錯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.61,0:13:30.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That guy? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 那傢伙嗎 - 是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:32.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heads up. Heads up.\N{\rCHT}注意 注意{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.82,0:13:35.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's up, guys?\N{\rCHT}大家好啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.55,0:13:38.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Looks like Christmas came early, huh?\N{\rCHT}耶誕節提前來囉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:40.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Ho, ho, ho. Where have you guys been?\N{\rCHT}是啊 你們死哪去了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:42.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, we went to a fucking Nickelback concert.\N{\rCHT}去聽"五分錢"的演唱會了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.47,0:13:44.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,How was it? Throw your panties on stage?\N{\rCHT}怎麼樣 有扔小褲褲嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:45.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nah, nah, nah,\N{\rCHT}不是啦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.83,0:13:47.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,we got stuck in a holding position till the weather broke.\N{\rCHT}我們一直等到放晴才起飛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:49.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,From what I hear, the weather here doesn't change until June.\N{\rCHT}聽說這種天氣 會持續到6月{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.65,0:13:51.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Snowed last night. So get used to it.\N{\rCHT}昨晚還下雪 趕快習慣吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:52.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What? Really? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 真的嗎 - 對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.14,0:13:54.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's all this?\N{\rCHT}這些是什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.33,0:13:56.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Someone gave the quartermaster a Gold Card.\N{\rCHT}有人給軍需官辦了金卡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.78,0:14:00.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, the only unit with any cold weather tac-gear is the 10th Mountain.\N{\rCHT}只有第10山地師有防寒裝備{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.14,0:14:01.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,They ain't sharing.\N{\rCHT}他們不分給別人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:02.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Make sure everyone carries a GPS.\N{\rCHT}要人手一個GPS{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.95,0:14:04.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I couldn't find one topo map of this place.\N{\rCHT}我找不到這裡的地形圖{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.75,0:14:07.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Copy that, Captain. - Hey, look what 515 left outside their tents.\N{\rCHT}- 知道了 - 你們看 515小隊把什麼留在門外{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.94,0:14:10.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, guys, quiet down. - Oh, it's Britney Spears!\N{\rCHT}- 大家安靜 - 小甜甜布蘭妮來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:12.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Five months in country, this hair is what you're getting, man.\N{\rCHT}來5個月頭髮就會變這樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.81,0:14:15.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, man. Is that a wig? Can I touch it? Just one time.\N{\rCHT}那是假髮嗎 可以摸一把嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.09,0:14:17.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ask Coffers' wife, man. She loves it.\N{\rCHT}問考佛的老婆 她愛死了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.23,0:14:21.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cap said grow it out, guys. What happened? What happened?\N{\rCHT}隊長叫我留發 結果就變這樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:24.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Whoa! Be careful! Vern knows Krav Maga!\N{\rCHT}小心喔 他會以色列防身術{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:26.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't even think about...\N{\rCHT}你少亂來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:35.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, pencils down.\N{\rCHT}好了 時間到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.55,0:14:38.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,The other five teams have been interviewed.\N{\rCHT}其他5隊都面試完了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.04,0:14:41.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,And, Cap, we're all countin' on you, so, you know,\N{\rCHT}隊長 我們就靠你了 所以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.12,0:14:43.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,- no pressure. - Thanks, buddy.\N{\rCHT}- 不必有壓力 - 謝謝你啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.53,0:14:46.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,- See you soon, boys. - Yep.\N{\rCHT}- 待會見 - 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.73,0:14:48.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give 'em hell, Cap.\N{\rCHT}給他們好看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:56.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bin Laden has been financing the Taliban and Al-Qaeda,\N{\rCHT}本·拉登 資助塔利班和基地組織{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.36,0:14:59.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,setting up terrorist training camps all over Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}在全阿富汗 設立恐怖分子訓練營{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:02.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's had one big win on U.S. soil.\N{\rCHT}他在美國大勝一場{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:04.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,He wants another.\N{\rCHT}他會食髓知味{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:07.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if we don't stop him, there will be more.\N{\rCHT}要是不阻止他 將會後患無窮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.08,0:15:10.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bin Laden might be the brains, but make no mistake about it,\N{\rCHT}本·拉登或許是主腦 但別搞錯了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:13.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,in Afghanistan, the Taliban is the muscle.\N{\rCHT}在阿富汗 是塔利班掌握武力{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.21,0:15:16.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we remove them from power,\N{\rCHT}要是推翻塔利班政權{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.74,0:15:18.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,he can't use them to make his attacks.\N{\rCHT}他就無法利用他們發動攻擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:20.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mazar-i-Sharif.\N{\rCHT}馬紮裡沙裡夫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:24.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whoever controls that city, controls Afghanistan. If we...\N{\rCHT}得那座城市者得阿富汗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:27.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,take Mazar from the Taliban, then we cripple Bin Laden.\N{\rCHT}我們拿下馬紮裡 就能讓本·拉登跛腳{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:30.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that's half-right.\N{\rCHT}這話對了一半{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.10,0:15:34.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you're gonna interrupt me, you should probably be entirely right.\N{\rCHT}你要打斷我 就應該完全說中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:36.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, we aren't taking anything.\N{\rCHT}不 我們什麼也不拿下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.88,0:15:39.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,The man who's gonna take Mazar is named General Dostum.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆將軍 會拿下馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.57,0:15:42.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's an Afghan warlord with the Northern Alliance.\N{\rCHT}他是北方聯盟的阿富汗軍閥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:44.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,He has the troops, he has the intel, he knows the cliffs.\N{\rCHT}他有軍隊 有情報 熟悉地形{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.77,0:15:47.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,He knows every cave and most importantly,\N{\rCHT}熟悉地勢 最重要的是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:49.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,he does not care for the Taliban.\N{\rCHT}他一點也不喜歡塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:51.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,So this is about airstrikes?\N{\rCHT}所以是要提供空襲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:53.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sorry, sir.\N{\rCHT}長官 抱歉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:55.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, you nailed that one.\N{\rCHT}不 這次你說對了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.57,0:15:58.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum cannot take out the Taliban by himself.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆一個人 扳不倒塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:15:59.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here's the plan.\N{\rCHT}計畫是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.36,0:16:01.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're gonna drop you into Northern Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}你們會空降到北阿富汗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.97,0:16:04.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,There, you will meet up with a CIA operative\N{\rCHT}再跟中情局密探會合{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.11,0:16:05.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,who will take you to Dostum.\N{\rCHT}去見杜斯塔姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:07.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your mission,\N{\rCHT}你們的任務{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:09.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,earn Dostum's trust,\N{\rCHT}是取得杜斯塔姆的信任{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,embed with his militia,\N{\rCHT}加入他的民兵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:15.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,you fight alongside him while he makes his way to Taliban strongholds.\N{\rCHT}與他並肩作戰 讓他攻向塔利班據點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.26,0:16:18.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,When you get there, you call in for close air support strikes.\N{\rCHT}到時你們就請求密接空援攻擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:20.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum will do the rest. One by one,\N{\rCHT}其他交給杜斯塔姆 一個接一個{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:22.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,stronghold by stronghold,\N{\rCHT}一個據點接一個據點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.52,0:16:25.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,until he takes Mazar, and the Taliban falls.\N{\rCHT}直到他拿下馬紮裡 塔利班垮臺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:26.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,You got six weeks.\N{\rCHT}你們有6周{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:29.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'd say three weeks, sir.\N{\rCHT}我會說是3周 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.23,0:16:31.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,- God damn it. - No, no.\N{\rCHT}- 可惡 - 沒關係{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.81,0:16:33.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll bite.\N{\rCHT}好 我聽你說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:35.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why three?\N{\rCHT}為什麼是3周{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:38.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Russians have been here before, right? They've done this.\N{\rCHT}俄國人也來這裡打過仗 對吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.04,0:16:39.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,And they wrote about it.\N{\rCHT}他們有記載{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:41.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,They said the snow was shutting down,\N{\rCHT}到了11月中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:43.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,all the mountain passes by mid-November.\N{\rCHT}大雪會阻斷所有山路{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:45.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Every year, without fail.\N{\rCHT}每年毫無例外{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.16,0:16:47.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, if the Russians are talking about a bad winter,\N{\rCHT}俄國人口中的嚴冬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:49.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's usually worth paying attention to, isn't it?\N{\rCHT}絕對值得留意{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.87,0:16:52.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,After three weeks, we will not get into Mazar.\N{\rCHT}要是3周後 進不了馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:55.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,That snow will hit, the Taliban will dig in, and my men won't come home.\N{\rCHT}雪一下 塔利班一躲 我們就回不了家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.81,0:16:59.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your air support comes from B-52s at 35,000 feet.\N{\rCHT}B-52轟炸機 由3萬5千尺高空投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.90,0:17:01.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,How do you think you're gonna get close enough to be accurate\N{\rCHT}你們要怎麼靠得夠近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.80,0:17:03.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,without parking a bomb in your lap?\N{\rCHT}又不會被炸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.45,0:17:04.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll have to get out of the way, sir.\N{\rCHT}當然是要讓開才行{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.32,0:17:08.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,The extra three weeks is cushion for your fuck-ups.\N{\rCHT}多出的3周 是以防萬一{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.51,0:17:10.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,There won't be any fuck-ups. Three weeks is all we need.\N{\rCHT}不會有萬一 3周就夠了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.72,0:17:13.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pretty confident for a guy who's never done this before.\N{\rCHT}真有自信啊 明明沒經驗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.69,0:17:14.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Never been to war.\N{\rCHT}也沒打過仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.94,0:17:16.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't see that as a disadvantage, sir.\N{\rCHT}我不認為這是劣勢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.81,0:17:19.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe you should explain that.\N{\rCHT}也許你應該說明一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.15,0:17:22.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're teaming up with a warlord that we know nothing about.\N{\rCHT}我們要跟一名完全陌生的軍閥聯手{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.03,0:17:25.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna be able to tell our enemies from our allies.\N{\rCHT}到時也無法分辨敵友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.51,0:17:26.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Every step we take is gonna be on a\N{\rCHT}那裡戰爭無數{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:28.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,minefield from a hundred different wars.\N{\rCHT}每一步都是敏感帶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.53,0:17:33.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,And no one's ever called in a smart bomb airstrike from a B-52. So\N{\rCHT}也沒人請求過B-52投擲導引炸彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:34.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,anyone who tells you they've done this\N{\rCHT}說執行過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.57,0:17:37.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,before or has experience in this is lying, sir.\N{\rCHT}有經驗的人 都是在說謊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.48,0:17:39.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no playbook here. We're gonna have to write it ourselves.\N{\rCHT}根本沒有前例 我們得自己應變{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:42.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,I briefed five\N{\rCHT}我跟5名隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:44.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,potential captains for this mission.\N{\rCHT}簡介了這次任務{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:48.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,About a hundred years of military experience between them.\N{\rCHT}他們加起來 有近百年的軍事經驗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:53.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,But you're the only one that sees it the way it is.\N{\rCHT}只有你看出這次任務的本質{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.40,0:17:56.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,I choose you. You and 11 men.\N{\rCHT}我選你 你和11名隊員{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:17:59.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Task Force Dagger.\N{\rCHT}你們是刺刀特遣隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:03.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would be remiss if I did not say to you, even in success\N{\rCHT}我有職責要告訴你 就算成功{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.55,0:18:06.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,the odds of you coming home...\N{\rCHT}你們回來的機率{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.13,0:18:08.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're 100%, sir, with all due respect.\N{\rCHT}是百分之百 長官 恕我直言{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.26,0:18:10.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,See, I kind of made a promise, too.\N{\rCHT}我自己也做了承諾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.32,0:18:12.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know better than that, Nelson.\N{\rCHT}你不該輕易承諾 尼爾森{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.26,0:18:15.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What'd she get you to? - Christmas.\N{\rCHT}- 她說什麼時候 - 耶誕節{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:18.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a hell of a thing we do, isn't it?\N{\rCHT}這是苦差事 不是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:22.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,How do you love your family and leave them to go to war?\N{\rCHT}離開心愛的家人去打仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:26.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're wheels up at 2200. Dismissed.\N{\rCHT}晚間10點直升機起飛 退下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:29.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no. Knock that off. Go.\N{\rCHT}不用多禮了 走吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:32.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Captain.\N{\rCHT}隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:39.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,The most important thing a man can take into combat is a reason why.\N{\rCHT}戰鬥最重要的動力 就是為何而戰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.88,0:18:43.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is from the towers.\N{\rCHT}這是雙塔的殘骸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.34,0:18:45.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,You carry that with you.\N{\rCHT}你帶在身上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:49.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Five weeks ago, 19 men attacked our country.\N{\rCHT}5周前 國家遭到19人攻擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.47,0:18:51.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,The 12 of you\N{\rCHT}你們12人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.08,0:18:54.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,will be the first ones to fight back.\N{\rCHT}將是第一波反攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.94,0:18:57.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go win this thing.\N{\rCHT}去打贏戰爭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:18:58.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\N{\rCHT}多謝長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.63,0:19:04.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah!\N{\rCHT}好耶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:06.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch. We're the first ones in!\N{\rCHT}媽的 我們打頭陣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:09.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's kind of like the Apollo program.\N{\rCHT}對啊 有點像阿波羅計畫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.14,0:19:11.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know what they sent into space first, right?\N{\rCHT}你知道最早上太空的是什麼吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.14,0:19:13.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What? Great. - A monkey.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼 好吧 - 一隻猴子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:14.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, listen, brother.\N{\rCHT}很好 不過你聽我說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.16,0:19:18.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,If it's six weeks, it's six weeks, okay? We can't rush this.\N{\rCHT}6周就6周好嗎 不能急{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:20.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're in harm's way no matter what the weather.\N{\rCHT}不管天氣怎樣都很危險{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.55,0:19:24.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,If your only goal is trying to keep us alive,\N{\rCHT}你如果一心只想保我們活命{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:25.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,we're dead men for sure.\N{\rCHT}我們就死定了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.81,0:19:28.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,I ain't losing one man on this team, Hal.\N{\rCHT}這支隊伍一個人也不能少 哈爾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.93,0:19:30.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,The only way home is winning.\N{\rCHT}想回家就只能贏{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.78,0:19:34.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, shit, I believe you.\N{\rCHT}靠 我信你了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.45,0:19:36.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's tell the boys we're up.\N{\rCHT}走吧 去通知大家要上陣了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:48.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God!\N{\rCHT}天哪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.01,0:19:53.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,This woman was stoned to death for being pregnant out of wedlock.\N{\rCHT}這個女人 因為未婚懷孕被石頭砸死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:56.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is what the Taliban does to women in Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}塔利班就是這樣對待女人的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.74,0:19:58.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, just shut that shit off.\N{\rCHT}天哪 關掉啦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.77,0:20:02.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's what they gave us for intel. - But that's not intel, that's motivation.\N{\rCHT}- 這是上面給的情報 - 那又不是情報 那是動機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:04.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I got two towers full of that.\N{\rCHT}我有整整兩棟高塔的動機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:06.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, you don't need to study, Falls.\N{\rCHT}不必研究啦 佛斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.47,0:20:08.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,You just shoot the guy shooting at you.\N{\rCHT}誰轟你 你就轟誰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:10.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that how that works? Thank you very much, Mr. Wizard.\N{\rCHT}是這樣嗎 謝謝你啊 老師{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.67,0:20:12.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, look, Michaels. It's you.\N{\rCHT}麥克斯你看 是你耶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:14.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, you guys are jealous.\N{\rCHT}靠 你們就是眼紅{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:17.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you call that? Is it like a coif or something?\N{\rCHT}那個是叫美髮嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.92,0:20:19.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Guys. Guys, guys. - I don't do bad hair.\N{\rCHT}- 喂 喂喂 - 大家注意{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.81,0:20:20.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen up!\N{\rCHT}各位{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.85,0:20:23.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, boys.\N{\rCHT}是我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:28.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's us, we're going in. - Yeah!\N{\rCHT}- 我們要進去 - 好耶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.48,0:20:30.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,We beat out the five other teams.\N{\rCHT}我們從6支隊伍中出線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:32.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're gonna drop in behind enemy lines,\N{\rCHT}將深入敵後{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:34.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,link up with a warlord of the Northern Alliance,\N{\rCHT}聯合北方聯盟軍閥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:35.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,General Abdul Dostum.\N{\rCHT}阿布杜爾·杜斯塔姆將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.13,0:20:38.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll assist him in fighting the Taliban\N{\rCHT}協助他對付塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.22,0:20:40.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,and taking back the city of Mazar-i-Sharif,\N{\rCHT}奪回馬紮裡沙裡夫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.82,0:20:42.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,which happens to be the stronghold\N{\rCHT}那是塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.16,0:20:44.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,and linchpin for the entire northern Taliban force.\N{\rCHT}在北方的據點和樞紐{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.13,0:20:47.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now if we don't take that city,\N{\rCHT}要是不拿下那座城市{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:48.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,the whole country will turn\N{\rCHT}全阿富汗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:50.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,into a goddamn terrorist training camp.\N{\rCHT}都會成為恐怖分子訓練營{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:52.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,World Trade Center's just the beginning.\N{\rCHT}世貿中心只是開始{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.31,0:20:54.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're not finished with us yet.\N{\rCHT}他們還沒鬧完{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.09,0:20:56.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,The catch is, we only have 21 days.\N{\rCHT}麻煩的是只有21天時間{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.13,0:20:58.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,How many troops does he have?\N{\rCHT}他有多少兵力{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.70,0:21:00.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's got about 200 paid soldiers\N{\rCHT}大約兩百名職業軍人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.47,0:21:02.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,and an undetermined number of part-time militia.\N{\rCHT}和人數不明的民兵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.70,0:21:04.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,What about the other side?\N{\rCHT}那對方呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.08,0:21:05.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,The other side has about\N{\rCHT}對方約有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.49,0:21:07.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,50,000 Taliban and Al-Qaeda fighters.\N{\rCHT}5萬塔利班和基地死士{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:11.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Missiles, armor, rockets, mortars, machine guns.\N{\rCHT}飛彈 裝甲部隊 火箭彈 迫擊炮 機關槍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:14.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We're outnumbered. - Just 5,000 to one.\N{\rCHT}- 我們勢單力薄 - 也就5千比1{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.82,0:21:16.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's what I call a target-rich environment.\N{\rCHT}這叫隨便打都是靶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:19.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I kind of like those odds, to be honest. - Now, gentlemen,\N{\rCHT}- 我喜歡這種優勢 - 各位{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.06,0:21:21.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,once we land, we're about nine hours away from help.\N{\rCHT}一旦落地 援軍要9小時才能到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.27,0:21:25.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which effectively means it doesn't exist. We're on our own.\N{\rCHT}也就是說援助並不存在 我們得靠自己{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:27.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,We all need to understand\N{\rCHT}大家都必須明白{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.45,0:21:30.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,that capture is not an option here.\N{\rCHT}當俘虜不在選項內{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.82,0:21:32.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,We've all seen the intel on what the\N{\rCHT}大家都看過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.32,0:21:34.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Taliban does to their prisoners, correct?\N{\rCHT}塔利班怎麼對待俘虜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.03,0:21:36.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those motherfuckers will make you suffer.\N{\rCHT}那些混蛋 會讓人生不如死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.98,0:21:39.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Shit goes south, I'm dying with my boots on. - Amen.\N{\rCHT}- 要是出差錯 我絕對要戰死 - 阿門{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:40.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,As am I.\N{\rCHT}我也是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.25,0:21:43.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,We go in tonight. Single ship, no backup.\N{\rCHT}我們今晚進去 一趟飛到 沒後援{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.72,0:21:45.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,So police your gear, get some rest.\N{\rCHT}大家好好整裝 休息一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.24,0:21:48.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Had a successful test flight?\N{\rCHT}之前試飛成功過嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.31,0:21:50.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,We are the test flight.\N{\rCHT}我們就是試飛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.81,0:22:39.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you die,\N{\rCHT}要是你死了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.36,0:22:43.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,that's a letter you and your wife are gonna wish you wrote.\N{\rCHT}你和你老婆 都會希望你留了信{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.00,0:22:47.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just made her a promise I'm coming home.\N{\rCHT}我才剛答應她會回家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.22,0:22:50.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,I ain't writing her a letter that says I broke it.\N{\rCHT}我才不要寫信說 我食言了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.49,0:23:12.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,We got one, two,\N{\rCHT}人員1 2{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:19.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess that space suit answers the question\N{\rCHT}你都穿太空衣了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:21.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,about closing the freaking doors.\N{\rCHT}看來不會關門{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.69,0:23:24.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's your cruising altitude? - That's a good question.\N{\rCHT}- 你們會飛多高 - 這是個好問題{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.98,0:23:28.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it must be above 10,000 feet if you're using O2.\N{\rCHT}你都戴氧氣罩了 一定有上萬尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.35,0:23:30.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit, the mountains we're flying over are 10,000 feet.\N{\rCHT}要飛越的山脈就有上萬尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:32.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,The sandstorms would ruin the engines\N{\rCHT}沙暴會破壞引擎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.68,0:23:34.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,and missiles have been fired from the peaks.\N{\rCHT}還遇過山峰上射出飛彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.54,0:23:36.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that puts us at 20.\N{\rCHT}那就是2萬尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.59,0:23:39.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't fly a Chinook at 20,000 feet.\N{\rCHT}契努克直升機飛不了2萬尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.22,0:23:40.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna.\N{\rCHT}不會的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.36,0:23:41.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Flight altitude's 25.\N{\rCHT}我們要飛到2萬5{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.06,0:23:43.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh.\N{\rCHT}哦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.54,0:23:45.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, how's this thing take it?\N{\rCHT}這玩意撐得住嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.26,0:23:46.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll find out.\N{\rCHT}待會就知道了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.48,0:23:47.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is there O2 for my team?\N{\rCHT}我的弟兄們有氧氣可吸嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.90,0:23:49.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,We got masks in the back, but they don't work.\N{\rCHT}後面有面罩 不過不管用{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.58,0:23:51.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hell, ours didn't work last flight.\N{\rCHT}上次我們的也不管用{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.14,0:23:52.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,This dipshit started seeing bogeymen.\N{\rCHT}這白癡都出現幻覺了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.74,0:23:54.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Almost crashed into the damn mountain.\N{\rCHT}差點就去撞山{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.90,0:23:57.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit. We're gonna go hypoxic.\N{\rCHT}靠 我們會缺氧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.52,0:23:58.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not me.\N{\rCHT}我不會{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.46,0:24:00.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keeping my eyes on that fucker right there.\N{\rCHT}我會死盯著駕駛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.93,0:24:02.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're going to the clouds, gentlemen.\N{\rCHT}我們要飛上雲霄了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.59,0:24:05.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one's ever flown a chopper this high this far.\N{\rCHT}沒有直升機飛過這麼高 這麼遠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.84,0:24:07.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Strap in tight!\N{\rCHT}系好安全帶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.40,0:24:10.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I've never been hypoxic before. - Really?\N{\rCHT}- 我從來沒缺氧過 - 是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.13,0:24:11.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's great.\N{\rCHT}很贊喔{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.73,0:24:13.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,All you do is faint.\N{\rCHT}就只是昏過去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.31,0:24:15.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Think of it as a nine-hour nap.\N{\rCHT}就當是睡了9小時{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.02,0:24:17.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not the going to sleep that worries me.\N{\rCHT}我擔心的不是睡著{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.54,0:24:19.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the goddamn hangover on the other side.\N{\rCHT}是醒來以後不舒服{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.59,0:24:20.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, baby!\N{\rCHT}好耶 寶貝{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.75,0:24:23.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, you know why the Army uses Chinooks, right?\N{\rCHT}你們知道 陸軍為什麼用契努克吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.36,0:24:24.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why?\N{\rCHT}為什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.51,0:24:27.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,So we'll be good and mad when we get into battle.\N{\rCHT}好讓我們火爆開戰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.87,0:24:31.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know, man! I'm a laugh factory!\N{\rCHT}我知道 我超爆笑的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.46,0:24:34.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mission equipment is set. EOS, flare, chaff.\N{\rCHT}行動裝備就緒 緊急供氧 熱誘彈 干擾箔{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.15,0:24:37.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,595, we are clear for takeoff.\N{\rCHT}595小隊 我們要起飛了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.85,0:24:43.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Silver wings upon their chest\N{\rCHT}胸前別著銀翼勳章{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.56,0:24:45.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,These are men\N{\rCHT}他們是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.36,0:24:47.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,America's best\N{\rCHT}美國的佼佼者{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.52,0:24:51.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,One hundred men we'll test today\N{\rCHT}今日接受考驗的100人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.62,0:24:55.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,But only three win the Green Beret\N{\rCHT}只有3人能戴上綠扁帽{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.60,0:25:26.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, 595, this is 1213.\N{\rCHT}1213呼叫595專機{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.25,0:25:27.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Visibility is deteriorating.\N{\rCHT}能見度惡化{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.03,0:25:39.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're turning back, blind alley.\N{\rCHT}我們要掉頭 沒辦法了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.99,0:26:07.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hang on! We're descending.\N{\rCHT}挺住 要下降了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.64,0:26:10.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,On purpose?\N{\rCHT}到了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.35,0:26:13.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,- On purpose? - Roger that.\N{\rCHT}- 到了嗎 - 收到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.13,0:26:15.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Wheels down, two minutes. - Two minutes!\N{\rCHT}- 2分鐘後降落 - 2分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.05,0:26:17.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Two minutes! - Wake up!\N{\rCHT}- 2分鐘 - 快醒來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.16,0:26:25.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jock up, NODs on!\N{\rCHT}整裝 戴上夜視鏡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.95,0:26:37.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right gunner has landing area in sight.\N{\rCHT}右門槍手 已看到降落地{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.56,0:26:38.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Going in hot.\N{\rCHT}準備好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.80,0:26:41.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here we go!\N{\rCHT}要到了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.72,0:26:43.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fifteen, ten, nine, eight. Hold your forward.\N{\rCHT}15 10 9 8 保持前進{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.09,0:26:46.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bring it down.\N{\rCHT}下降{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.34,0:26:50.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cleared on left, cleared on right.\N{\rCHT}左邊安全 右邊安全{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.24,0:26:52.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,On five, four, three. Ramps cleared down.\N{\rCHT}倒數5 4 3 艙門安全{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.56,0:26:53.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ramp, ramp, ramp.\N{\rCHT}開艙門{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.42,0:27:37.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第1天 北阿富汗 馬紮裡沙裡夫南方40哩處
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.29,0:27:47.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N{\rCHT}喂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.61,0:27:48.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,There.\N{\rCHT}那邊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.32,0:27:51.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,- See those two fellas? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 有看到那兩個人 - 有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.84,0:27:54.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Is this our escort? - No, I don't think so.\N{\rCHT}- 是護送人員嗎 - 應該不是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.80,0:27:56.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to be meeting a squad.\N{\rCHT}來的應該是一支小隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.65,0:27:58.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't think these are our guys.\N{\rCHT}我覺得不是他們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.02,0:28:18.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shut them up.\N{\rCHT}讓他們安靜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.76,0:28:22.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put your fucking weapons down!\N{\rCHT}快把武器放下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.03,0:28:25.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Drop your weapons!\N{\rCHT}放下武器{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:30.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,No! No! No! Friendlies! Friendlies!\N{\rCHT}不不不! 是友軍! 友軍!{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.19,0:28:31.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stand down!\N{\rCHT}解除戒備{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.42,0:28:33.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, weapons down!\N{\rCHT}把武器放下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.09,0:28:38.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let them up. That's your fucking escort.\N{\rCHT}讓他們起來 他們是護送人員{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.33,0:28:39.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let them up.\N{\rCHT}讓他們起來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.64,0:28:44.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're sorry.\N{\rCHT}對不起{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.19,0:28:55.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you could just tell him we apologize?\N{\rCHT}可以跟他說 我們很抱歉嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.02,0:29:03.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You team leader?\N{\rCHT}你是隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.17,0:29:04.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I am. You guys are late.\N{\rCHT}對 你們來晚了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.52,0:29:05.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, we're here now.\N{\rCHT}現在來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.45,0:29:07.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't speak Dari?\N{\rCHT}你不會說達利語{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.56,0:29:09.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Not at all. - How's your Uzbek?\N{\rCHT}- 不會 - 烏茲別克語呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.74,0:29:11.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,So-so. My Russian's decent.\N{\rCHT}普通 俄語還不錯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.26,0:29:13.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Well, Russian will get you through. We should move,\N{\rCHT}會俄語就行了 我們該走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.25,0:29:15.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's a long hike. They dumped you in a bad spot.\N{\rCHT}要長途跋涉 你們的降落點不好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.68,0:29:17.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's go, grab your gear. Let's move.\N{\rCHT}好 帶上裝備出發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.29,0:29:21.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Back up! No! No!\N{\rCHT}退後 不要碰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.73,0:29:28.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.14,0:30:06.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is it.\N{\rCHT}到了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.72,0:30:08.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,They call it the Alamo.\N{\rCHT}這裡叫阿拉莫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.98,0:30:10.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Got you set up in here.\N{\rCHT}你們的營房在這邊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.89,0:30:12.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you guys take first watch.\N{\rCHT}你們兩個先站哨{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.28,0:30:14.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rotate every two hours. Head on a swivel.\N{\rCHT}每2小時換班 隨時留意周遭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.61,0:30:15.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Roger that. - On it.\N{\rCHT}- 知道了 - 沒問題{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.98,0:30:20.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know everyone died in the Alamo, right?\N{\rCHT}你知道 阿拉莫戰役是全軍覆沒吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.59,0:30:23.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think you should keep that to yourself.\N{\rCHT}這種事還是別說出來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.21,0:30:31.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is great.\N{\rCHT}這個贊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.49,0:30:33.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is gonna go over real well in a Muslim country.\N{\rCHT}在穆斯林國家 絕對受歡迎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.47,0:30:35.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,It ain't our job to choose the gifts, man. It's yours.\N{\rCHT}挑選禮物 是你的工作{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.07,0:30:39.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on in.\N{\rCHT}進來吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.30,0:30:40.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is your new home.\N{\rCHT}這是你們的新家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.42,0:30:43.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, feel free to eat any of that.\N{\rCHT}要吃什麼別客氣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.58,0:30:46.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,The bread's good. I don't know what this is, but it's fucking great.\N{\rCHT}麵包很棒 我不知道這是什麼 但超好吃{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.08,0:30:48.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give me the lay of the land.\N{\rCHT}跟我說一下狀況{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.69,0:30:50.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,What kind of intel you got?\N{\rCHT}你有什麼情報{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.08,0:30:52.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, here's what I know, and it ain't much.\N{\rCHT}我知道的如下 而且不多{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.18,0:30:54.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's left of the Northern Alliance is essentially\N{\rCHT}北方聯盟基本上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.81,0:30:56.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,three separate militias.\N{\rCHT}剩下3批民兵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.32,0:30:58.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right? That are all enemies with each other.\N{\rCHT}懂嗎 他們互相為敵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.38,0:31:01.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,General Dostum, General Atta, and General Mohaqiq.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆將軍 阿塔將軍 莫哈奇克將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.33,0:31:04.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you got a three-pronged attack that doesn't communicate,\N{\rCHT}所以現在是三頭馬車 互不溝通{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.08,0:31:05.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,will not assist each other.\N{\rCHT}互不協助{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.54,0:31:06.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if they meet on the battlefield,\N{\rCHT}在戰場上遇到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.82,0:31:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,they'll probably stop fighting the Taliban and\N{\rCHT}八成會扔下塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.69,0:31:09.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,start killing each other.\N{\rCHT}開始互相殘殺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.03,0:31:12.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,What about our contact, General Dostum?\N{\rCHT}我們的接頭人 杜斯塔姆將軍呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.13,0:31:14.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,General Abdul Rashid Dostum.\N{\rCHT}阿布杜爾·拉希德·杜斯塔姆將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.65,0:31:16.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, he's Uzbek.\N{\rCHT}他是烏茲別克人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.11,0:31:20.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Started fighting the Russians when he was 16. He's 55 now.\N{\rCHT}16歲開始打俄國人 現在55歲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.43,0:31:22.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we have his bio. What's he like?\N{\rCHT}我們知道他的生平 他人怎麼樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.31,0:31:24.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's he like? - Yeah,\N{\rCHT}- 人怎麼樣 - 對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.78,0:31:27.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,what's he like? His personality. Angry, happy, sad?\N{\rCHT}人怎麼樣 他的性格 兇暴 開朗 憂鬱{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.44,0:31:30.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He likes show tunes. - He likes show tunes. Great.\N{\rCHT}- 他喜歡歌舞劇曲目 - 他喜歡歌舞劇曲目 很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.19,0:31:31.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, I read people for a living,\N{\rCHT}我專門揣摩別人的心思{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.89,0:31:34.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,and I can't get a bead on this guy. Okay?\N{\rCHT}但我完全摸不透他 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.66,0:31:36.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Only two things I know for sure.\N{\rCHT}我只確定兩件事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.32,0:31:39.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,He hates the Taliban and they hate the shit out of him.\N{\rCHT}他恨塔利班 塔利班恨死他{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.31,0:31:41.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,How worried should we be about any of these guys\N{\rCHT}我們是否要擔心 他們有人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.68,0:31:43.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,trying to sell us to the Taliban?\N{\rCHT}想把我們賣給塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.51,0:31:45.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Uh, I'd be pretty fucking worried, if I was you.\N{\rCHT}如果是我會挺擔心的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.28,0:31:47.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right.\N{\rCHT}好吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.35,0:31:49.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Does Dostum speak English? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 杜斯塔姆會說英語嗎 - 不會{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.65,0:31:51.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,He speaks Tajik.\N{\rCHT}他會說塔吉克語{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.45,0:31:54.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,He speaks Uzbek. He speaks Dari.\N{\rCHT}烏茲別克語 達利語{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.62,0:31:57.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,He speaks Pashtun, which is what the Taliban speak.\N{\rCHT}會說塔利班說的普什圖語{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.63,0:32:00.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,And he speaks Russian. So you got that going for ya.\N{\rCHT}還有俄語 所以你有這個優勢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.40,0:32:01.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you with us through this?\N{\rCHT}你要一起執行任務嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.79,0:32:03.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I'm leaving right now.\N{\rCHT}不 我現在就要走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.23,0:32:04.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,I got a 50 kilometer hike\N{\rCHT}我要跋涉50公里{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.67,0:32:06.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,to give a bag of money to another warlord.\N{\rCHT}給另一個軍閥送錢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.96,0:32:09.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who knows, maybe we'll see each other on the battlefield.\N{\rCHT}搞不好 我們會在戰場上相遇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.58,0:32:10.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we do,\N{\rCHT}到時{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.90,0:32:13.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,don't shoot the guy in the backwards cap.\N{\rCHT}可別對反戴帽子的人開槍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.29,0:32:14.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll keep that in mind.\N{\rCHT}我們會記住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.80,0:32:20.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,God, that spook is cheery.\N{\rCHT}好一個開朗的間諜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.02,0:32:23.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, runnin' around here alone, setting this thing up?\N{\rCHT}獨自在這裡 奔走安排這件事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.63,0:32:26.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Say one thing about him,\N{\rCHT}可以肯定的是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.88,0:32:28.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,he's got giant balls.\N{\rCHT}他實在膽大包天{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.72,0:32:31.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N{\rCHT}喂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.28,0:32:34.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So where is he? - Who?\N{\rCHT}- 他人在哪裡 - 誰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.01,0:32:35.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.10,0:32:37.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,No clue.\N{\rCHT}不清楚{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.79,0:32:39.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,He knows we're here though, right?\N{\rCHT}但他知道我們來了吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.90,0:32:41.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whole fucking country knows you're here.\N{\rCHT}全阿富汗都知道你們來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.83,0:32:46.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Best of luck, Captain.\N{\rCHT}祝你們好運 隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.64,0:32:47.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean it.\N{\rCHT}真心的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.00,0:32:49.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,You too.\N{\rCHT}也祝你好運{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.23,0:32:50.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give 'em hell.\N{\rCHT}給他們死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.62,0:33:09.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come look at this.\N{\rCHT}你們來看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.05,0:33:12.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Graveyard of Empires,\N{\rCHT}帝國的墳場{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.11,0:33:13.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we're in it.\N{\rCHT}我們就在其中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:18.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shows you how unlucky it is to write on that wall, so\N{\rCHT}可見在那面牆寫字 很不吉利{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.95,0:33:20.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,no one better do it.\N{\rCHT}最好不要有人手賤{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.59,0:33:30.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, Cap.\N{\rCHT}隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.34,0:33:32.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get some rest, all right?\N{\rCHT}你休息一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.04,0:33:34.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Something ain't right here. - Now, look.\N{\rCHT}- 情況不太對勁 - 聽著{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.25,0:33:39.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is about being smart, not super human.\N{\rCHT}我們要聰明行事 而不是當超人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.05,0:33:40.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know, I know.\N{\rCHT}我知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.23,0:33:42.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna take the next watch.\N{\rCHT}下一個輪我站哨{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.58,0:33:47.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Massoud.\N{\rCHT}馬蘇德{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.38,0:33:51.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,When he died, the Northern Alliance might have died with him.\N{\rCHT}他一死 北方聯盟差點也垮了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.01,0:33:57.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第2天 阿拉莫 馬紮裡沙裡夫南方34哩處
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.88,0:34:15.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move! Move!\N{\rCHT}快出去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.77,0:34:17.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move!\N{\rCHT}走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.73,0:34:18.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,That Dostum?\N{\rCHT}是杜斯塔姆嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.45,0:34:51.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,General.\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.42,0:34:53.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Peace be with you.\N{\rCHT}祝你平安{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.88,0:35:06.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,And what did he say?\N{\rCHT}他說什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.65,0:35:08.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,He said it's good to know the language of your enemies.\N{\rCHT}他說會講敵人的語言是好事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.99,0:35:30.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Am I doing this alone?\N{\rCHT}我要一個人去嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.64,0:35:31.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go.\N{\rCHT}大家走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.76,0:35:33.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Looks like Spencer got a promotion.\N{\rCHT}看來斯賓塞升官了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.64,0:35:35.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess he prefers brunettes.\N{\rCHT}我猜他偏愛棕發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.62,0:35:37.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seems that way, huh?\N{\rCHT}看樣子是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.74,0:35:58.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, why don't we give him the gift?\N{\rCHT}把禮物送上吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.10,0:36:06.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,飼料 給馬的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.65,0:36:23.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的馬謝謝你
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.04,0:36:26.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,What did he say?\N{\rCHT}他說什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.28,0:36:28.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't think the horse feed's a big hit.\N{\rCHT}馬飼料的反應不佳{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.26,0:36:30.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that went over like a bag of shit.\N{\rCHT}感覺跟收到一袋大便一樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.29,0:36:32.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,You wanna try the vodka, Captain?\N{\rCHT}要不要試試伏特加{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.73,0:36:40.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,General.\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:36:58.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,To our new American friends.\N{\rCHT}敬我們的新美國朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.25,0:37:05.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I hope they don't think they win\N{\rCHT}但願他們不會以為{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.78,0:37:07.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,copying the Russians.\N{\rCHT}學俄國人就贏了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.03,0:37:09.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was told you didn't speak English.\N{\rCHT}我聽說你不說英語{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.96,0:37:12.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't speak to the man who told you I don't.\N{\rCHT}我沒對你問的那個人說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.85,0:37:16.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where are my bombs?\N{\rCHT}我的炸彈在哪裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.24,0:37:19.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, I have more bombs than you could ever want.\N{\rCHT}將軍 我的炸彈多到超乎需求{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.96,0:37:21.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Could you show me the Taliban's location? - Why the young one speak?\N{\rCHT}- 請你告訴我塔利班 - 為什麼是年輕人說話{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.86,0:37:23.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's our captain, sir.\N{\rCHT}他是隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.59,0:37:29.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Tell them to stand down. - Hey, Diller.\N{\rCHT}- 叫他們退下 - 迪勒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.75,0:37:39.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, I'm the captain.\N{\rCHT}將軍 我是隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.34,0:37:41.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is my team. You speak to me, all right?\N{\rCHT}這是我的隊伍 你要跟我談 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.25,0:37:45.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- This is my country. - I understand that.\N{\rCHT}- 這是我的國家 - 我明白{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.57,0:37:48.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,You own the land, but we own the sky.\N{\rCHT}你制地 但我們制空{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.56,0:37:50.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,You want our bombs, talk to me.\N{\rCHT}你想要我們的炸彈 就跟我談{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.08,0:37:53.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.63,0:37:54.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,We talk.\N{\rCHT}我們談{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.50,0:37:56.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why\N{\rCHT}這些人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.11,0:37:58.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,these men follow you?\N{\rCHT}為什麼追隨你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.10,0:38:00.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,I could ask you the same question.\N{\rCHT}我也可以這樣反問你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.19,0:38:02.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't want the answer.\N{\rCHT}你不會想知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.28,0:38:05.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look.\N{\rCHT}你看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.20,0:38:08.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look. Those eyes.\N{\rCHT}看啊 那雙眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.30,0:38:10.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Killer eyes.\N{\rCHT}殺手的眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.32,0:38:16.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those eyes.\N{\rCHT}那雙眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.93,0:38:18.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Killer eyes.\N{\rCHT}殺手的眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.79,0:38:20.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}沒錯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.48,0:38:22.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Killer eyes.\N{\rCHT}殺手的眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.12,0:38:25.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,What\N{\rCHT}你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.02,0:38:27.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,did you kill?\N{\rCHT}殺過什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.71,0:38:30.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,You wanna see me kill?\N{\rCHT}想看我開殺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.37,0:38:32.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,You take me to the Taliban, I'll show you.\N{\rCHT}帶我去打塔利班 就讓你見識{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.11,0:38:38.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.56,0:38:39.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,We go.\N{\rCHT}我們走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.30,0:38:42.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,That was easy.\N{\rCHT}這倒容易{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.77,0:38:47.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Buddy, you better check that fucking swagger\N{\rCHT}兄弟 你最好摸清那混蛋{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.91,0:38:49.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,before he sells us to the highest bidder.\N{\rCHT}免得他把我們高價賣出{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.54,0:38:52.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, he needed to know how far I can be pushed. Now he does.\N{\rCHT}他知道我的底線了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.92,0:38:54.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fucking killer's eyes.\N{\rCHT}去他的殺手眼睛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.23,0:39:00.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,General.\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.44,0:39:02.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, how far away is the Taliban?\N{\rCHT}塔利班離這裡多遠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.31,0:39:05.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Five hours. I have horses for you.\N{\rCHT}5小時 我準備了馬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.49,0:39:09.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's only six. I need 12. I got 12 men.\N{\rCHT}只有6匹 12人要12匹{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.44,0:39:10.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have six.\N{\rCHT}我只有6匹{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.10,0:39:13.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, Cap.\N{\rCHT}隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.65,0:39:15.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Looks like he's not done pushing you.\N{\rCHT}看來他還要踩你底線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.41,0:39:19.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't like splitting up the team, Hal.\N{\rCHT}我不喜歡分頭行動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.22,0:39:21.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it was bound to happen sooner or later, might as well be now.\N{\rCHT}遲早要分 現在分也好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.69,0:39:23.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,At least he's willing to fight.\N{\rCHT}至少他願意打{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.14,0:39:25.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,I figured he'd just milk us for supplies and money.\N{\rCHT}我還以為他只想A物資和錢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.37,0:39:30.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can you show me on the map exactly where we're going?\N{\rCHT}你可以指給我看要去哪裡嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.26,0:39:34.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cobaki. Over the mountains.\N{\rCHT}寇巴基 山的另一邊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.71,0:39:38.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, Diller, Coffers,\N{\rCHT}迪勒 考佛 麥克斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.44,0:39:40.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Michaels, Bennett, Jackson, you're with me.\N{\rCHT}麥克斯 貝內特 傑克森跟我去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:43.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Falls, Black, grab the daypacks, extra ammo.\N{\rCHT}佛斯 布萊克 背包多帶些彈藥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.86,0:39:46.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,I took Dehi\N{\rCHT}我4天前{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.39,0:39:48.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,four days ago from Taliban.\N{\rCHT}從塔利班手中攻下德希{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.64,0:39:49.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mullah Razzan,\N{\rCHT}塔利班的領袖{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.07,0:39:53.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,leader of the Taliban, has a high price on your heads.\N{\rCHT}穆拉·拉贊 出高價懸賞你們人頭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.49,0:39:56.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,100,000 US dollars for your body.\N{\rCHT}一具屍體10萬美元{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.33,0:39:59.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,50,000 for your bloody uniforms.\N{\rCHT}染血制服5萬美元{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.93,0:40:00.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's it?\N{\rCHT}就這樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.17,0:40:04.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,A little low.\N{\rCHT}有點低耶{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.74,0:40:06.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Toss a little change out, Taliban.\N{\rCHT}加點價嘛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.40,0:40:08.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, look on the bright side.\N{\rCHT}往好的方面想{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.16,0:40:09.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,If his plan was to cash us in,\N{\rCHT}他要是想賣我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.82,0:40:12.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,he'd find another six horses for sure. I guarantee it.\N{\rCHT}絕對會把馬備齊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.16,0:40:15.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, who's ridden before? Anyone?\N{\rCHT}好 有誰騎過馬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.72,0:40:17.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Summer camp, when I was nine.\N{\rCHT}9歲參加夏令營騎過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.49,0:40:20.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cancun, spring break. But I was pretty drunk.\N{\rCHT}春假去墨西哥玩 不過我喝醉了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.70,0:40:21.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't ride for shit.\N{\rCHT}我完全不會騎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.03,0:40:23.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's nobody.\N{\rCHT}所以就是沒人騎過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.77,0:40:26.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, hey, this will be fun. All right.\N{\rCHT}不過會很好玩的 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.37,0:40:32.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, so a kick means "go". This is the steering wheel.\N{\rCHT}踢馬腹就是走 韁繩是方向盤{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.77,0:40:34.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Left to go left, right to go right.\N{\rCHT}左扯左轉 右扯右轉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.72,0:40:36.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Pull back to stop. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 向後扯是停 - 好的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.47,0:40:38.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's not waiting for us. Saddle up.\N{\rCHT}他沒等我們 上馬吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.81,0:40:41.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll start a supply chain, okay? Schedule a drop.\N{\rCHT}我會開一條補給線 安排空投物資{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.98,0:40:43.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Does it have a name?\N{\rCHT}它叫什麼名字嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.03,0:40:44.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Request ammo for Dostum's men. - I know,\N{\rCHT}- 幫他要彈藥 - 我知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.86,0:40:46.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,but does it have a name?\N{\rCHT}它叫什麼名字{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.01,0:40:48.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,And Michaels will be on the radio. We'll check in every four hours.\N{\rCHT}麥克斯負責無線電 每4小時回報{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.96,0:40:51.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He's gonna test you. - Yeah. I'm gonna test him, too.\N{\rCHT}- 他會測試你 - 是啊 我也會測試他{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.75,0:40:53.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure that's a good idea.\N{\rCHT}那樣不太好吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.65,0:40:54.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,About to find out.\N{\rCHT}很快就知道了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.50,0:40:58.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, fuck. God damn it.\N{\rCHT}真要命{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.32,0:41:00.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good luck, boys.\N{\rCHT}祝大家好運{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.61,0:41:02.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,You guys look like a bunch of naturals.\N{\rCHT}這架勢 完全是天生好手{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.08,0:41:04.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't break the horse, Dill.\N{\rCHT}別把馬騎垮了 迪勒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.74,0:41:05.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.78,0:41:17.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,貝沙姆近郊 塔利班佔領第3年
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.84,0:41:34.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.63,0:41:39.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你很勇敢 我看得出來
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.47,0:41:42.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.02,0:41:47.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道那種脖子很長的動物嗎?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.94,0:41:53.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,長頸鹿
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.61,0:41:54.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,答對了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.49,0:41:58.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,長頸鹿怎麼拼?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.79,0:42:12.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,看著我
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.72,0:42:21.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,真聰明
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.35,0:42:27.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,有沒有人能告訴我
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.40,0:42:31.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,15乘以8
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.73,0:42:35.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,等於多少?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.28,0:42:43.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.17,0:42:54.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,求你 穆拉·拉贊 求求你
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.13,0:42:58.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,求求你 不要這樣 以真主之名
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.01,0:43:02.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,看在真主的分上 拜託不要
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.48,0:43:10.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,看在真主的分上
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.74,0:43:21.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,要堅強
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.99,0:43:24.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,真主是偉大的
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.01,0:43:48.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們都知道他的聖訓
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.35,0:43:51.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,年齡超過
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.77,0:43:53.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,8歲的女孩
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.48,0:43:55.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,不得受教育
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.19,0:43:58.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們想要老師?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.15,0:44:03.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在你們學到了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:14.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,德希村 馬紮裡沙裡夫南方32哩處
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.26,0:44:30.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't like how they're looking at us, Cap.\N{\rCHT}我不喜歡他們看我們的眼神{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.85,0:44:35.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cap, we got three AK's and a spotter at three o'clock.\N{\rCHT}3點鐘方向 有3把AK47和觀測員{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.41,0:44:38.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I see it.\N{\rCHT}我看到了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.81,0:44:47.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What the fuck are we stopping for? - I don't know.\N{\rCHT}- 我們停下來幹嘛 - 不知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.00,0:44:53.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Supplies.\N{\rCHT}補給物資{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.07,0:44:54.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, we're sitting ducks here.\N{\rCHT}我們在這裡是甕中鱉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.01,0:44:56.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding me.\N{\rCHT}開玩笑的吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.74,0:44:59.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Risking our asses for 10 gallons of water.\N{\rCHT}為了10加侖水賭我們的命{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.31,0:45:00.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, he's showing us off.\N{\rCHT}他是在炫耀我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.56,0:45:03.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's saying, "Look at the Americans."\N{\rCHT}他在說 "看這些美國人"{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.43,0:45:04.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,"They're here with me."\N{\rCHT}"他們來挺我了"{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.54,0:45:20.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't fucking look down!\N{\rCHT}不要往下看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.64,0:45:22.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where you look, the horse goes.\N{\rCHT}你看哪 馬就走哪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.72,0:45:25.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move your head, it shifts your weight and shifts the horse's weight.\N{\rCHT}頭一動 你和馬的重心就跟著動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.78,0:45:27.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Got it? - Yeah, yeah, I got it.\N{\rCHT}- 懂嗎 - 好 懂了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.46,0:45:45.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,分遣A隊595小隊A組 科巴基山洞
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.05,0:45:49.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, boss. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 老大 - 怎樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.05,0:45:54.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's got us on the north side of this range.\N{\rCHT}他把我們帶到山北了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.14,0:45:55.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm guessing that isn't good. - No.\N{\rCHT}- 我猜不是好事 - 對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.65,0:45:57.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Commo satellites orbit to the south.\N{\rCHT}通訊衛星往南運行{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.33,0:46:00.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no way I'm gonna get any signal through that mountain range.\N{\rCHT}隔著山脈 絕對收不到訊號{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.08,0:46:02.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna have to go up on the plateau and try to get better contact.\N{\rCHT}我得上高原去 設法取得通訊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.76,0:46:04.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's got us camping in a dead spot.\N{\rCHT}他把我們帶到死角紮營{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.54,0:46:07.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,You think he knows it's a dead spot?\N{\rCHT}他知道這是死角{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.55,0:46:10.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know every cell phone dead zone in my hometown.\N{\rCHT}我老家每個收訊死角我都知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.16,0:46:12.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,No GPS either, huh?\N{\rCHT}GPS也沒訊號{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.70,0:46:14.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, it's pretty shitty.\N{\rCHT}對 訊號很差{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.41,0:46:23.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your men are too slow.\N{\rCHT}你的人 動作太慢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.54,0:46:26.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,We will kill the Taliban in the morning.\N{\rCHT}我們早上就去殺塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.26,0:46:36.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第4天 595小隊B組 阿拉莫營地
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.15,0:46:38.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,I see you.\N{\rCHT}我看到你了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.06,0:46:40.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know it. I see that.\N{\rCHT}好 我知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.93,0:46:43.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's a cool musket.\N{\rCHT}好酷的毛瑟槍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.97,0:46:48.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Najeeb? Cool, I'm gonna take a piss now, so...\N{\rCHT}納吉布 好 我要撒尿了 所以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.69,0:46:50.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no. No.\N{\rCHT}不要{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.38,0:46:52.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like to do this alone, bro.\N{\rCHT}我喜歡自己尿{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.02,0:46:55.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Respect the culture.\N{\rCHT}尊重一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.69,0:46:59.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,This fucking kid.\N{\rCHT}死小孩{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.09,0:47:03.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Milo? - What's up, bro?\N{\rCHT}- 米洛 - 怎樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.61,0:47:05.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Looks like you got a shadow.\N{\rCHT}看來你有跟班了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.76,0:47:06.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.86,0:47:15.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You see Dostum's men ride up that mountain today? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你看到他們行軍了嗎 - 有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.70,0:47:18.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Had his whole army ready to travel in five minutes.\N{\rCHT}全軍出發不用5分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.36,0:47:22.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,My guess is the Taliban ain't much different. It's not gonna be easy.\N{\rCHT}我猜塔利班也差不多 這是場硬仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.28,0:47:23.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, these people are tough.\N{\rCHT}這些人很強悍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.61,0:47:26.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,How do you know so much about horses?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼會這麼懂馬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.49,0:47:29.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I grew up on a ranch.\N{\rCHT}我是農場小孩{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.67,0:47:31.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Father taught me.\N{\rCHT}我爸教我的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.59,0:47:35.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,About the only thing he was ever good and gentle with were horses.\N{\rCHT}他大概只有對馬溫柔和善過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.98,0:47:37.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,So the old man ruled with an iron fist?\N{\rCHT}所以是拳頭教育{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.64,0:47:40.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,And a leather belt. Anything he could get his hands on.\N{\rCHT}還有皮帶 拿到什麼用什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.10,0:47:41.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?\N{\rCHT}是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.24,0:47:43.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Must have been best friends with my old man. - Oh, yeah?\N{\rCHT}- 那他跟我爸一定是拜把 - 是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.78,0:47:46.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I hope they let us see this one through, you know?\N{\rCHT}希望上面讓我們完成任務{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.81,0:47:49.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Afghanistan's been invaded\N{\rCHT}2千年來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.28,0:47:51.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,for the last 2,000 years repeatedly by everyone.\N{\rCHT}阿富汗一再遭到各方入侵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.11,0:47:54.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Genghis Khan, Alexander the Great...\N{\rCHT}成吉思汗 亞歷山大大帝{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.27,0:47:55.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've been reading up on the place?\N{\rCHT}你研究這裡了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.85,0:47:57.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was a history teacher.\N{\rCHT}我原本是歷史老師{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.97,0:48:01.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Get the fuck out! - No! I swear to God! Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 少來了 - 我發誓 是真的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.39,0:48:04.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit, that's right. No, I remember reading something about it.\N{\rCHT}靠 我也記得有看到過{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.29,0:48:06.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,In your report. It wasn't long though.\N{\rCHT}你檔案裡有 但時間不長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.21,0:48:07.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,What happened? I didn't...\N{\rCHT}怎麼了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.40,0:48:10.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,I got into a fight with this guy who was harassing my girlfriend,\N{\rCHT}有人騷擾我女朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.66,0:48:12.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,you know. And I kind of beat him up pretty bad.\N{\rCHT}被我抓來打 打得蠻重的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.82,0:48:15.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,And where I was headed, I was headed to jail. So,\N{\rCHT}眼看著要去坐牢了 所以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.45,0:48:16.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,I chose the military.\N{\rCHT}我選擇從軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.32,0:48:19.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit, man.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.70,0:48:22.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,And here you are years later sitting in a cave.\N{\rCHT}多年後 你坐在這個山洞裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.17,0:48:23.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I should have chose jail.\N{\rCHT}早知道去坐牢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.78,0:48:27.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why do your men stand guard?\N{\rCHT}你的人為什麼站哨{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.32,0:48:30.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're my guests, I protect you.\N{\rCHT}你們是客人 我保護你們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.94,0:48:33.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're not just your guests, General. We're your allies.\N{\rCHT}我們不只是客人 還是盟友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.70,0:48:36.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,My men aren't standing guard against you. They're standing with you.\N{\rCHT}我的人不是防你們 是一起防守{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.47,0:48:38.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is my responsibility.\N{\rCHT}這是我的責任{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.26,0:48:40.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is how we're trained. We have orders to follow.\N{\rCHT}我們受過訓練 要服從命令{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.91,0:48:43.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's the difference between you and me.\N{\rCHT}這就是你我的差別{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.50,0:48:46.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have many men over you.\N{\rCHT}你上面有很多人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.04,0:48:49.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Over me, only God.\N{\rCHT}我上面 只有神{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.43,0:48:57.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,God, that was,\N{\rCHT}真是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.08,0:49:00.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,- that was some real bonding right there. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 感情大升溫啊 - 是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.00,0:49:05.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sir.\N{\rCHT}長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.80,0:49:08.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sitrep from Spencer.\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞傳來現場報告{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.66,0:49:11.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's requesting a supply drop for Dostum's men.\N{\rCHT}他請求 為杜斯塔姆的人空投物資{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.42,0:49:13.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Winter's coming, and they need gear and provisions.\N{\rCHT}快入冬了 他們需要裝備和糧食{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.93,0:49:15.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, ship it out. Where's Nelson?\N{\rCHT}運過去 尼爾森呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:18.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not sure. Terraings cutting off radio reception.\N{\rCHT}不確定 地勢阻斷無線電收信{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.56,0:49:22.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,He thinks that Nelson's en route to Dostum's HQ.\N{\rCHT}他覺得他們 正前往杜斯塔姆的總部{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.30,0:49:26.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Our best guess is here. Cobaki.\N{\rCHT}我們推測是這裡 科巴基{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.33,0:49:28.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, hold on. Why aren't Nelson and Spencer together?\N{\rCHT}等等 尼爾森和斯賓塞怎麼沒在一起{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.00,0:49:31.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nelson split the team. He took six men\N{\rCHT}尼爾森把人分組 他帶6人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.38,0:49:33.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,and left Spencer and the others at the recon point.\N{\rCHT}留斯賓塞和其他人在偵察點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.81,0:49:35.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Christ, why'd he do that?\N{\rCHT}真是的 為什麼要這樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.26,0:49:36.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum only gave him six horses.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆只給他6匹馬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.95,0:49:38.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently, that's the only way to cross the mountains.\N{\rCHT}有馬才能翻山越嶺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.08,0:49:40.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,According to Spencer,\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.33,0:49:42.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,the horses aren't just transportation.\N{\rCHT}馬匹不只是交通工具{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.88,0:49:45.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Spencer says Dostum relies on them for combat.\N{\rCHT}他說杜斯塔姆還靠它們打仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.87,0:49:46.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Horses?\N{\rCHT}騎馬打仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.31,0:49:48.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\N{\rCHT}是的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.09,0:49:53.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔利班佔領之貝沙姆村 馬紮裡沙裡夫南方28哩處
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.33,0:49:58.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,There. Mullah Razzan's men.\N{\rCHT}穆拉·拉贊的兵在那裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.54,0:50:00.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wait, where?\N{\rCHT}等等 哪裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.27,0:50:05.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see the pickup trucks?\N{\rCHT}你看那些皮卡車{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.34,0:50:08.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those are the Taliban forces outside of Bescham.\N{\rCHT}那就是他們部署在村外的兵力{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.50,0:50:11.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right. Okay, General, let me explain how this works.\N{\rCHT}好的將軍 我跟你說明一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.30,0:50:13.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need to be close enough to give the exact coordinates and elevation.\N{\rCHT}我得靠近 才能提供準確座標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.91,0:50:14.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's too dangerous.\N{\rCHT}太危險了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.05,0:50:17.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, we're too far away. I can't call in anything from here.\N{\rCHT}這樣太遠 我無法從這裡請求空援{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.80,0:50:20.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,500 of my men can die\N{\rCHT}我每折損五百人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.24,0:50:22.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,before one American gets a scratch.\N{\rCHT}才能有一個美國人受皮肉傷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.82,0:50:24.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You know why? - No, why, sir?\N{\rCHT}- 你知道為什麼 - 為什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.72,0:50:26.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because if one American die,\N{\rCHT}要是有一個美國人死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.75,0:50:29.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,your government leaves, and then we lose the war.\N{\rCHT}你們政府會離開 我們就輸掉戰爭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.84,0:50:33.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'm dropping these bombs from 30,000 feet.\N{\rCHT}好 投彈高度是3萬尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.23,0:50:34.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,The plane doesn't guide the bombs, I do.\N{\rCHT}導引炸彈的不是飛機 是我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.84,0:50:36.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I can't get close enough, I can't call in the exact location.\N{\rCHT}要是不夠靠近 就無法提供{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.56,0:50:37.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give me your little map.\N{\rCHT}把你的小地圖給我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.34,0:50:39.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give me your map.\N{\rCHT}給我啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.01,0:50:45.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,There. See? Here. Taliban.\N{\rCHT}那裡 看到沒 這裡 塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.46,0:50:48.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Here. Taliban. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 這裡 塔利班 - 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.68,0:50:51.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,And here, Taliban.\N{\rCHT}還有這裡 塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.53,0:50:52.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now drop your bomb.\N{\rCHT}丟炸彈吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.95,0:50:54.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He's not getting it. - And we're still too far away.\N{\rCHT}- 他沒聽懂 - 這樣還是太遠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.83,0:50:57.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Drop bombs. - How do I even know this is the Taliban?\N{\rCHT}- 丟炸彈 - 我怎麼知道他們是塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.83,0:50:59.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who else would it be?\N{\rCHT}不然會是誰{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.14,0:51:00.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of armies in these mountains, General,\N{\rCHT}這裡有很多支軍隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.85,0:51:02.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the U.S. is only at war with one of them.\N{\rCHT}只有一支是美國的敵軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.06,0:51:06.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You call me a liar? - I'm not saying that. I'm just saying that\N{\rCHT}- 你說我是騙子 - 不是這個意思{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.10,0:51:07.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,we're so far away I can't even tell\N{\rCHT}我只是說距離太遠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.86,0:51:09.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,what we're shooting at, what we're hitting.\N{\rCHT}連炸到什麼都不知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.67,0:51:15.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,拉贊 我跟美國人在一起 他們要來殺你了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.56,0:51:17.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Christ, he's calling the fucking Taliban.\N{\rCHT}靠 他在聯絡塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.80,0:51:21.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想知道你們是塔利班
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.39,0:51:25.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟他們說你們是 我們好宰了你們
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.37,0:51:27.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,America, fuck you!\N{\rCHT}去你的美國人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.72,0:51:31.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,See? Drop bombs.\N{\rCHT}看吧 丟炸彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.27,0:51:40.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Badger 17, this is Alpha 595.\N{\rCHT}595小隊A組 呼叫獾17{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.41,0:51:42.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,We need a drop on enemy position.\N{\rCHT}請對敵軍陣地投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.34,0:51:46.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,8-4-7-2, 6-5-4-3. How copy? Over.\N{\rCHT}8472 6543 收到了嗎 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.57,0:51:49.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Alpha 595, I copy.\N{\rCHT}595小隊A組 收到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.48,0:51:52.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,8-4-7-2, 6-5-4-3, over.\N{\rCHT}8472 6543 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.87,0:51:54.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Roger. Drop when ready.\N{\rCHT}收到 準備好就投擲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.37,0:51:56.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,You hit the green on this one, boss, you're a goddamn wizard.\N{\rCHT}要是這次能丟中 老大你就神了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.92,0:51:58.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no shit.\N{\rCHT}可不是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.96,0:52:39.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.04,0:52:42.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, someone explain to these guys we missed.\N{\rCHT}誰來跟他們說沒丟中{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.43,0:52:44.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就說吧 你們這群蠢驢
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.66,0:53:00.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Goddamn. Shit.\N{\rCHT}媽的 靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.78,0:53:01.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,死王八蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.76,0:53:04.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That was ridiculous. - I didn't come here to play around.\N{\rCHT}- 太扯了 - 我可不是來玩的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.85,0:53:06.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Check fire, we're way off.\N{\rCHT}暫停投彈 差太遠了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.74,0:53:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stay here, I'll call back coordinates.\N{\rCHT}留在這裡 我會傳回座標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.32,0:53:11.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no, Nelson.\N{\rCHT}不行 尼爾森{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.27,0:53:14.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Where's Cap going? - I don't know. Coffers.\N{\rCHT}- 隊長要去哪 - 不知道 考佛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.58,0:53:15.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm getting closer.\N{\rCHT}我要靠近點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.21,0:53:53.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wasn't gonna let you have all the fun.\N{\rCHT}怎麼能讓你一個人過癮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.67,0:53:58.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,You ready for new coordinates?\N{\rCHT}準備接收新座標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.64,0:54:00.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we got some anxious people up here.\N{\rCHT}好 這裡氣氛很緊張{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.13,0:54:06.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bad element maneuvered in on 'em.\N{\rCHT}有敵軍靠近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.40,0:54:08.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Captain, there's an element moving in on you.\N{\rCHT}隊長 有敵軍靠近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.16,0:54:19.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, stay here. Let's go!\N{\rCHT}你們待著 我們走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.43,0:54:58.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll say again. 8-3-9...\N{\rCHT}我再說一遍 839{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.72,0:55:05.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Clear and hot.\N{\rCHT}可以投擲了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.80,0:55:11.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bombs inbound, boys. Let's move!\N{\rCHT}炸彈要來了 夥計們 快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.24,0:55:15.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're danger close, Cap!\N{\rCHT}隊長 我們在射程內{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.66,0:55:17.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move back! Move!\N{\rCHT}撤退 快點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.33,0:55:21.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move! Move!\N{\rCHT}快走 快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.03,0:55:50.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,拉贊 你完蛋了
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.98,0:55:53.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,General.\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.49,0:55:56.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Their forward position's obliterated.\N{\rCHT}前沿陣地已清除{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.16,0:55:57.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why aren't we moving on the village?\N{\rCHT}為什麼不進攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.16,0:56:01.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,You will not live long here if you ignore what I'm telling you.\N{\rCHT}在這裡不聽我的話 就活不久{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.27,0:56:03.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,You told me to bomb, that's what I did. Why aren't we attacking?\N{\rCHT}你叫我炸我炸了 為什麼不進攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.87,0:56:05.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,That wasn't the plan today.\N{\rCHT}那不是今天的計畫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.46,0:56:06.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mind telling me the plan?\N{\rCHT}可以把計畫告訴我嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.80,0:56:10.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,We attack tomorrow.\N{\rCHT}我們明天進攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.84,0:56:15.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow. Great. So that was, uh, what?\N{\rCHT}明天 好 那剛才是什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.27,0:56:17.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Nice little dress rehearsal? - A rehearsal, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 先彩排一下 - 彩排 是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.92,0:56:18.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Great.\N{\rCHT}很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.24,0:56:40.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna negotiate.\N{\rCHT}我才不跟你議價{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.55,0:56:42.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,These are my boots.\N{\rCHT}這是我的靴子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.15,0:56:45.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, the ones you stole from our drop?\N{\rCHT}是你偷我們的空投物資{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.96,0:56:48.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that means.\N{\rCHT}我聽不懂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.92,0:56:51.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I bet you we haven't even found half our shit. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 我們找到的一定不到一半 - 嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.22,0:56:56.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. That roof looks familiar, doesn't it?\N{\rCHT}那個屋頂還真眼熟{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.17,0:56:59.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, how much, huh?\N{\rCHT}喂 多少錢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.28,0:57:03.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is that? $10? $9.50?\N{\rCHT}那是多少 10塊 9.5塊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.92,0:57:04.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Huh?\N{\rCHT}啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.07,0:57:08.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,They got 10% of our MREs, a quarter of our blankets.\N{\rCHT}他們拿走十分之一口糧 四分之一毛毯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.33,0:57:10.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're missing a lot.\N{\rCHT}東西少很多{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.92,0:57:14.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?\N{\rCHT}怎樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.00,0:57:21.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Guess they like our chem suits.\N{\rCHT}他們喜歡我們的防毒衣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.83,0:57:22.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tres chic.\N{\rCHT}時尚有型{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.28,0:57:54.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'd like to tell you it gets easier, but...\N{\rCHT}我很想說習慣了就好 但是{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.52,0:58:02.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know,\N{\rCHT}你知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.12,0:58:06.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,every now and then, you meet a guy who doesn't feel anything.\N{\rCHT}時不時 就會有那種無感的人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.61,0:58:11.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,He goes out there, he kills people.\N{\rCHT}衝鋒陷陣 殺人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.45,0:58:14.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Falls asleep before his head hits the pillow.\N{\rCHT}回來還沒躺好 就睡著了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.00,0:58:20.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, I used to think that that'd be better, right?\N{\rCHT}我以前 都覺得那樣比較好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.34,0:58:24.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,That maybe I was just too weak.\N{\rCHT}也許我就是太軟弱{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.38,0:58:28.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then I realized... Nah.\N{\rCHT}後來我明白了 不對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.11,0:58:33.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's the thing that reminds us that we're humans.\N{\rCHT}有這種感覺才算是人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.42,0:58:51.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第6天 B組 阿拉莫營地
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.81,0:58:57.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, here we go.\N{\rCHT}回來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.54,0:58:58.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,How'd you make out?\N{\rCHT}結果怎麼樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.25,0:59:01.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,- All kinds of goodies. - Good.\N{\rCHT}- 大豐收 - 很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.14,0:59:03.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Get most of it back? - It was like shopping at Macy's.\N{\rCHT}- 大多都找回來了 - 跟去瘋狂購物一樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.90,0:59:06.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, yo, Spence, bro. See that little kid over there?\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞 你看那個小孩{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.09,0:59:08.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.14,0:59:10.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't even take a piss without the kid up in my business.\N{\rCHT}我撒泡尿 他都要跟{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.30,0:59:13.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it is pretty fascinating.\N{\rCHT}不是挺好的嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.23,0:59:14.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, not really. It's not.\N{\rCHT}不 一點也不好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.83,0:59:17.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,No. He follows me around like a little stray dog, bro.\N{\rCHT}他跟流浪狗一樣跟前跟後{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.65,0:59:19.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you stop giving him treats?\N{\rCHT}你別再給他東西吃了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.32,0:59:21.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bro, that's the thing. I don't give him shit, all right?\N{\rCHT}問題是我根本沒有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.07,0:59:24.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,He just follows me around smiling with his little 1910 gun, bro.\N{\rCHT}他就一直拿把古董槍跟著我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.20,0:59:25.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't get it, do you?\N{\rCHT}你不懂對吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.05,0:59:27.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,What, Spence?\N{\rCHT}懂什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.23,0:59:29.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,These guys guard us.\N{\rCHT}他們在保護我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.57,0:59:31.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Any one of us gets killed,\N{\rCHT}要是我們有人死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.95,0:59:34.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum might execute the man he thinks is\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆會殺人究責{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.01,0:59:35.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,responsible and his whole family.\N{\rCHT}還株連全家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.40,0:59:40.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,And this poor boy got you.\N{\rCHT}這可憐的小孩 就是分到你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.68,0:59:43.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,So be nice.\N{\rCHT}對他好一點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.13,0:59:45.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Be nice.\N{\rCHT}對他好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.54,0:59:48.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you are...\N{\rCHT}你要不要{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.10,0:59:51.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, uh, Najeeb?\N{\rCHT}喂 納吉布{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.14,0:59:54.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, bro, I...\N{\rCHT}拿去 孩子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.07,0:59:57.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,got you a little... It's a little sucker.\N{\rCHT}這支棒棒糖給你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.83,0:59:58.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put it in your mouth.\N{\rCHT}放到嘴巴裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.39,1:00:07.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no! You take the thing off it.\N{\rCHT}不 不是 先拆掉包裝紙{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.76,1:00:09.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then you put it in your mouth.\N{\rCHT}然後 再放進嘴巴{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.07,1:00:12.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.Put it in your mouth. Yeah.\N{\rCHT}對 放進嘴巴 對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.52,1:00:15.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't even fucking go there, bro. Don't go there, bro.\N{\rCHT}你給我閉嘴 少囉唆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.62,1:00:17.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Give me my shoes. - That's cute.\N{\rCHT}- 把我的鞋子給我 - 好可愛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.23,1:00:18.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Shut up. - It's cute.\N{\rCHT}- 閉嘴 - 可愛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.18,1:00:21.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is their next objective, Bescham.\N{\rCHT}這是他們下一個目標 貝沙姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.65,1:00:24.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's only one way in, and the Taliban know it.\N{\rCHT}要攻只有一條路 塔利班知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.16,1:00:26.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're dug in hard just outside\N{\rCHT}他們在村外{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.94,1:00:28.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,of town right here, heavily fortified.\N{\rCHT}這裡 挖掩體修築防禦工事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.33,1:00:30.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,The whole fucking thing's a buzzsaw, sir.\N{\rCHT}情勢非常危險{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.76,1:00:32.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, then why the hell is Nelson walking into it?\N{\rCHT}那尼爾森為什麼要自投羅網{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.42,1:00:34.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.33,1:00:36.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did I pick the wrong guy?\N{\rCHT}我選錯人了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.18,1:00:39.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sir, this one's not on Nelson. It's geography.\N{\rCHT}這個由不得尼爾森 是地理使然{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.74,1:00:43.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bescham is the only way to Mazari.\N{\rCHT}貝沙姆 是往馬紮裡的必經之路{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.00,1:00:45.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, maybe so. But we can't pin all our hopes on Nelson.\N{\rCHT}也許是 但我們不能全指望尼爾森{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.36,1:00:48.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's get a second team in the works.\N{\rCHT}讓第二支小隊準備{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.46,1:00:51.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,If Dostum doesn't make it to Bescham by the time the weather sets in,\N{\rCHT}要是杜斯塔姆 沒在入冬前攻下貝沙姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.43,1:00:53.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's gonna be a real shitshow.\N{\rCHT}事情就嚴重了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.67,1:00:59.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔利班佔領之貝沙姆
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.49,1:01:03.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, B-52s are in position.\N{\rCHT}將軍 B-52就位了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.37,1:01:07.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have any idea what's going on?\N{\rCHT}現在是什麼情況{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.24,1:01:10.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum need to find out if his nephew still\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆在查他外甥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.20,1:01:12.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,over there, fighting along with Taliban.\N{\rCHT}是否還在塔利班陣營裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.35,1:01:13.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Many switch sides.\N{\rCHT}很多人會換邊站{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.94,1:01:15.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,For necessity, loyalty change.\N{\rCHT}效忠誰全看需求{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.97,1:01:17.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some every other week.\N{\rCHT}有些人兩周變一次{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.37,1:01:20.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why the hell would they do that?\N{\rCHT}為什麼要那樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.14,1:01:22.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,A lot of these guys are farmers.\N{\rCHT}很多人都是農民{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.06,1:01:24.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Taliban comes through, they torture, murder,\N{\rCHT}塔利班來了 又打又殺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.05,1:01:25.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,force them to fight. What choice do they have?\N{\rCHT}逼他們打仗 他們有的選嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:30.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is it just me or does it feel like\N{\rCHT}是我想太多{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.64,1:01:33.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,these assholes are counting their money every time they look at us?\N{\rCHT}還是這些人 每次看我們都在估價{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.58,1:01:39.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,General.\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.71,1:01:44.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,His nephew left this morning. We can proceed.\N{\rCHT}他外甥早上走了 可以繼續了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.93,1:01:46.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh. Great.\N{\rCHT}哦 很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.88,1:01:48.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,War's back on, guys.\N{\rCHT}戰爭重新開始了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.58,1:01:50.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, we're minutes from range.\N{\rCHT}將軍 敵人就在眼前{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.13,1:01:51.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is there anything you can tell me so I can\N{\rCHT}有沒有情報{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.35,1:01:53.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- better prepare my men to assist you? - Very good.\N{\rCHT}- 能讓我們做好準備 - 很好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.33,1:02:00.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know if horses were the best idea today.\N{\rCHT}今天騎馬好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.48,1:02:02.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,The bombs are gonna scare them bad.\N{\rCHT}炸彈會嚇到它們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.43,1:02:05.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,The horses know that these are American bombs.\N{\rCHT}馬知道那是美國炸彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.15,1:02:06.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,They won't be afraid.\N{\rCHT}它們不會怕{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.82,1:02:07.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, they know\N{\rCHT}它們知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.42,1:02:10.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,that they're American bombs. Okay.\N{\rCHT}是美國炸彈 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.62,1:02:12.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.\N{\rCHT}說得通啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.73,1:02:15.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wookie-99, new grid.\N{\rCHT}武技99 新座標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.31,1:02:40.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,拉贊 狗崽子 美國人會宰了你
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.56,1:02:42.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eastern flank is clear, General.\N{\rCHT}將軍 東側安全了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.11,1:02:45.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,You Americans, stay here!\N{\rCHT}美國人留在這裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.30,1:03:04.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,孬種 你們幹嘛?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.92,1:03:10.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're surrendering. Razzan is shooting his own men.\N{\rCHT}他們要投降 拉贊在殺自己人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.24,1:03:11.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.\N{\rCHT}真是的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.16,1:03:25.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, where the hell did those come from?\N{\rCHT}哪來的坦克車{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.04,1:03:29.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,How did Dostum not know about a supply line?\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆怎麼會不知道有補給線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.30,1:03:36.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wookie-99, we need a drop.\N{\rCHT}武技99 請求投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.67,1:03:38.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Negative. I'm bingo.\N{\rCHT}無法投彈 我沒油了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.01,1:03:39.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're kidding me! I'm staring at a company of tanks.\N{\rCHT}別鬧了 來了一堆坦克車{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.88,1:03:42.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We need a drop! - I'm sorry, I'm out of fuel, sir. I'm out.\N{\rCHT}- 我們需要投彈 - 抱歉 我沒油了 我得走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.59,1:04:19.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, they're getting slaughtered. We gotta cover their retreat.\N{\rCHT}他們被壓著打 我們得掩護撤退{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.69,1:04:21.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Michaels, Coffers, base element.\N{\rCHT}麥克斯和考佛留守{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.24,1:04:54.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go!\N{\rCHT}快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.79,1:05:12.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum!\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.40,1:05:15.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,We've lost air support! Fall back!\N{\rCHT}空援走了 快撤退{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.82,1:05:22.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fall back!\N{\rCHT}撤退{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.74,1:05:24.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennett! Bennett, are you okay?\N{\rCHT}貝內特 你還好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.51,1:05:36.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you have killer eyes!\N{\rCHT}現在你有殺手的眼睛了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.57,1:05:40.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go!\N{\rCHT}快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.69,1:05:46.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Fucking hold him still, man. - I'm fucking holding him.\N{\rCHT}- 把他按好 - 我有啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.32,1:05:48.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.\N{\rCHT}真是的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.89,1:06:04.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's move him up. Up there.\N{\rCHT}把他抬到那上面{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.63,1:06:17.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,General,\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.15,1:06:19.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,you know this area, right?\N{\rCHT}這一帶你很熟對吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.77,1:06:21.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right?\N{\rCHT}對吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.71,1:06:24.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which means you knew about the Taliban's supply line,\N{\rCHT}也就是說 你知道有補給線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.18,1:06:25.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,and you didn't tell me.\N{\rCHT}卻沒告訴我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.41,1:06:26.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I had known, if you had told me,\N{\rCHT}要是讓我知道{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.75,1:06:29.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I could have hit that column before they ever made it to us.\N{\rCHT}我就能在援軍來之前襲擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.48,1:06:33.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you wanna kill your own men, that's fine.\N{\rCHT}你要讓你的人去送死請便{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.29,1:06:35.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I aingt letting you put my men in harm's way, you understand?\N{\rCHT}但你別想害我的人身陷險境 懂嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.86,1:06:37.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everywhere you go is harm's way.\N{\rCHT}這裡到處都是險境{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.78,1:06:38.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,No shit.\N{\rCHT}是嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.26,1:06:43.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're fighting with horsemen against tanks.\N{\rCHT}我們跟騎兵 一起打坦克{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.06,1:06:46.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have an obligation to tell me everything you know.\N{\rCHT}你有義務 說出你知道的一切{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.26,1:06:48.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't have a stomach for everything I know.\N{\rCHT}我說得出 你也承受不起{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.15,1:06:49.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, fuck.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.81,1:06:51.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,You will not win here\N{\rCHT}你在這裡贏不了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.71,1:06:53.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,because you are not honest with yourself.\N{\rCHT}因為你對自己不誠實{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.32,1:06:56.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,You expect victory without blood.\N{\rCHT}你想要不流血就勝利{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.99,1:07:00.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I expect you to share strategic information with us.\N{\rCHT}我想要你 跟我們分享戰略情報{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.61,1:07:02.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Otherwise what the fuck are we doing here?\N{\rCHT}否則我們來幹嘛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.33,1:07:04.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your anger comes from your fear\N{\rCHT}你的憤怒來自恐懼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.58,1:07:06.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,because you live in a place where life\N{\rCHT}因為在你們那裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.58,1:07:08.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,looks better than afterlife.\N{\rCHT}今生比來世好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.28,1:07:09.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not this place.\N{\rCHT}這裡不一樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.04,1:07:12.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, Taliban kills everything you live for.\N{\rCHT}塔利班會消滅你所有的寄託{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.61,1:07:17.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your mission will fail because you fear death.\N{\rCHT}你的任務會失敗 因為你怕死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.30,1:07:21.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mullah Razzan's men, the Taliban,\N{\rCHT}穆拉·拉贊的兵 塔利班{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.45,1:07:23.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,they welcome it.\N{\rCHT}他們視死如歸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.70,1:07:28.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because they believe there is riches waiting for them in Heaven.\N{\rCHT}因為他們相信 天堂有財富相迎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.64,1:07:31.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give me the goddamn information I need,\N{\rCHT}把我需要的情報告訴我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.38,1:07:33.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,and I'll reward every last one of them.\N{\rCHT}我就讓他們全都變富翁{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.16,1:07:37.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, I'm your link\N{\rCHT}將軍 我在協助你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.98,1:07:40.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,to the greatest weaponry in the history of civilization.\N{\rCHT}使用文明史上最強軍備{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.36,1:07:43.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gotta stop guarding me and start trusting me.\N{\rCHT}你得放下戒心 信任我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.02,1:07:46.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Greatest weapon in history\N{\rCHT}史上最強的武器{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.51,1:07:47.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,is this.\N{\rCHT}是這個{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.67,1:07:50.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't have soldiers in my army,\N{\rCHT}我的軍隊裡沒有兵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.71,1:07:52.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,not one. Only warriors.\N{\rCHT}一個也沒有 只有戰士{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.28,1:07:56.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stop being a soldier.\N{\rCHT}別再當軍人了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.81,1:07:59.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Start using this,\N{\rCHT}要用心{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.34,1:08:02.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,and you can be a warrior, too.\N{\rCHT}那樣你也能成為戰士{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.23,1:08:23.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come with me.\N{\rCHT}跟我來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.83,1:08:45.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sit.\N{\rCHT}坐下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.73,1:08:52.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,They bring their weapons through Tiangi Gap.\N{\rCHT}他們走天吉峽谷 運送武器{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.80,1:08:55.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Out here, there's nothing.\N{\rCHT}峽谷外什麼也沒有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.10,1:08:59.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,No passage, no water. No shade.\N{\rCHT}沒通道 沒水源 沒有遮蔽{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.62,1:09:01.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,So the only way to Mazar-i-Sharif\N{\rCHT}想去馬紮裡沙裡夫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.69,1:09:03.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,is through Tiangi Gap.\N{\rCHT}只能走天吉峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.19,1:09:05.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's a choke point.\N{\rCHT}那是個咽喉點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.77,1:09:07.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's the only way.\N{\rCHT}那是唯一的路{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.14,1:09:11.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So, for us to take Mazar, we'll have to beat him in this Gap. - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 要攻下馬紮裡 就得在峽谷擊敗他 - 對{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.43,1:09:14.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,To get access to their stronghold in Tiangi,\N{\rCHT}要進入他們在峽谷的據點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.51,1:09:16.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,we must first take Bescham.\N{\rCHT}就得先攻下貝沙姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.88,1:09:21.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, you have the sky,\N{\rCHT}你們有制空權{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.02,1:09:24.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,but wars are won in the dirt.\N{\rCHT}但戰爭是在地上贏的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.42,1:09:28.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,I knew about their supply line.\N{\rCHT}我知道那裡有補給線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.80,1:09:30.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I didn't expect their weapons.\N{\rCHT}但我沒料到有那些武器{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.23,1:09:33.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fakir\N{\rCHT}法基爾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.73,1:09:34.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,was my godson.\N{\rCHT}是我的教子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.10,1:09:39.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Every time you lose a man,\N{\rCHT}每次失去手下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.67,1:09:42.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's like a stab in your heart.\N{\rCHT}都是椎心之痛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.75,1:09:46.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,And my heart is butchered, my friend.\N{\rCHT}我的心已經千瘡百孔 朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.01,1:09:50.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't think I send my men out there to die.\N{\rCHT}別以為我是讓我的人去送死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.00,1:09:57.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going to win you this thing, I swear to God.\N{\rCHT}我對天發誓 我會幫你打贏{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.35,1:10:03.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,I believe you.\N{\rCHT}我相信你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.99,1:10:07.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now see, the Taliban won't be defendingtheir western flank\N{\rCHT}塔利班不會防守西側{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.58,1:10:10.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,because they can't imagine anything coming from this desert.\N{\rCHT}一片荒地怎麼會有人攻來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.78,1:10:12.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, it's a crazy idea, but...\N{\rCHT}我有個很扯的想法 但{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.88,1:10:15.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,- But what? - Well, the Taliban reinforcements come through here.\N{\rCHT}- 但是什麼 - 塔利班的增援都走這裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.94,1:10:17.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Through the Tiangi Gap.\N{\rCHT}天吉峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.93,1:10:20.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is why Dostum's killing himself trying to move forward.\N{\rCHT}所以杜斯塔姆才拼了命要挺進{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.90,1:10:22.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,All the Taliban has to do is hold him off\N{\rCHT}塔利班只要抵擋到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.85,1:10:24.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,long enough to bring in more artillery.\N{\rCHT}運來更多炮彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.89,1:10:28.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's nothing out there. There's no water, no nothing.\N{\rCHT}峽谷外一片荒涼 沒水源 什麼也沒有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.22,1:10:32.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,When you come in behind their line, you cut that chain.\N{\rCHT}你們到了敵後 就切斷補給線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.16,1:10:34.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ammo dumps, convoys, anything you can hit, you hit it.\N{\rCHT}彈藥堆 車隊 有什麼就炸什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.74,1:10:37.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can I walk it? I'm sick of that fucking horse.\N{\rCHT}可以走路嗎 我受夠那匹馬了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.24,1:10:40.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Diller, it's 120 klicks or something.\N{\rCHT}那是120公里的路程{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.13,1:10:43.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,A drop would give up your position. You gotta pack everything in.\N{\rCHT}空投會暴露行蹤 物資得全帶上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.03,1:10:46.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Can Dostum give us some mules? - Yeah, probably.\N{\rCHT}- 杜斯塔姆可以提供騾子嗎 - 應該可以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.31,1:10:49.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Okay. - But listen, whoever does this thing has got to understand,\N{\rCHT}- 好 - 不過執行者必須明白{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.17,1:10:51.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,this is different than what we've been doing, all right?\N{\rCHT}這次任務不一樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.06,1:10:53.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're on your own. No reinforcements, no extraction, nothing.\N{\rCHT}只能靠自己 沒有援軍 不能退出{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.33,1:10:58.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit, I can't order anyone to do this.\N{\rCHT}我不能下這個命令{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.09,1:11:00.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Someone's got to volunteer.\N{\rCHT}得有人自告奮勇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.40,1:11:02.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, you can.\N{\rCHT}你當然可以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.08,1:11:04.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just give us the order.\N{\rCHT}你就下令吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.28,1:11:10.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's an order.\N{\rCHT}這是命令{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.56,1:11:11.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nothing I'd rather do.\N{\rCHT}樂意之至{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.41,1:11:13.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now pick two guys.\N{\rCHT}你挑兩個人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.42,1:11:16.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Bennett. - I'm in.\N{\rCHT}- 貝內特 - 我去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.80,1:11:19.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Coffers? - Oh, I thought you'd never ask.\N{\rCHT}- 考佛 - 哦 還以為你不會問我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.74,1:11:21.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Thank you, sir. - No, thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 謝謝長官 - 我才要謝你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.03,1:11:24.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good luck, Bennett.\N{\rCHT}祝你好運{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.93,1:11:26.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give 'em hell, buddy.\N{\rCHT}給他們死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.02,1:11:28.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess the best-looking fellas get the choice...\N{\rCHT}帥哥才有選擇的餘地{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.72,1:11:33.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第8天 B組 阿拉莫營地
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.44,1:11:39.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,595 Bravo, come in.\N{\rCHT}呼叫595小隊B組{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.18,1:11:42.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go for Bravo.\N{\rCHT}請說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.39,1:11:44.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, did you guys get horses? - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 你們有馬嗎 - 有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.07,1:11:46.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, good. Ride up to us.\N{\rCHT}很好 來找我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.93,1:11:49.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I split the team again, sent Diller downrange.\N{\rCHT}我又分組 把迪勒派出去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.55,1:11:51.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Roger that. On our way.\N{\rCHT}收到 馬上出發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.27,1:12:08.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the Ritz, boys.\N{\rCHT}歡迎光臨麗池大飯店{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.34,1:12:11.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Valet will take your horses in the back.\N{\rCHT}泊車小弟會把馬拉到後面{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.18,1:12:13.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Came all the way up here for this?\N{\rCHT}大老遠來這種地方{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.21,1:12:15.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where's the pool?\N{\rCHT}游泳池呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.34,1:12:16.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Trying to work on my suntan, bro.\N{\rCHT}人家最近在努力曬黑{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.94,1:12:18.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think my massage is at 4:00.\N{\rCHT}我應該是約4點按摩{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.08,1:12:22.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,What the hell happened to Spencer?\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞人呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.31,1:12:24.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, he was right behind us, Cap.\N{\rCHT}就在後面 隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.26,1:12:25.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh.\N{\rCHT}哦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.64,1:12:26.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.72,1:12:29.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You all right? - Oh, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你還好嗎 - 還好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.21,1:12:32.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm fine. I gotta get off this goddamn horse.\N{\rCHT}還好 只是得下馬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.09,1:12:35.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's his back. He slipped a disc, I think.\N{\rCHT}他的背受傷 應該是椎間盤突出{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.68,1:12:36.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.\N{\rCHT}好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.35,1:12:38.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give me your...\N{\rCHT}把你的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.46,1:12:41.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I got you. Okay.\N{\rCHT}我抱住你了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.44,1:12:44.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Easy. Jesus Christ! - Fuck!\N{\rCHT}- 放輕鬆 - 靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.40,1:12:46.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fucking heavy.\N{\rCHT}你重死了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.19,1:12:48.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sorry.\N{\rCHT}對不起{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.19,1:12:49.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're all right. You're good.\N{\rCHT}沒事了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.08,1:12:52.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, listen. Diller, he missed his first check-in.\N{\rCHT}迪勒錯過第一次回報時間{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.17,1:12:55.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it's the mountains. No reception, right?\N{\rCHT}山區的關係 收不到信號{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.47,1:12:56.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, maybe.\N{\rCHT}可能吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.59,1:12:57.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where'd you send him?\N{\rCHT}你派他去哪裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.85,1:12:59.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's flanking their supply route.\N{\rCHT}他要去破壞補給路線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.63,1:13:01.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Risky. - Little bit.\N{\rCHT}- 很冒險 - 有一點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.96,1:13:03.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, the band's back together.\N{\rCHT}又重新會師了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.42,1:13:07.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus, chief, you look like my grandpa.\N{\rCHT}天啊 大哥 你好像我爺爺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.97,1:13:09.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,20 bucks if you can stand up straight.\N{\rCHT}站得直 就給你20塊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.61,1:13:12.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can keep that $20.\N{\rCHT}你留著吃飯吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.99,1:13:15.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, the best thing about calling in airstrikes,\N{\rCHT}請求空襲最大的優點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.73,1:13:17.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,you can do it laying down, right?\N{\rCHT}就是可以躺著幹 對吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.55,1:13:18.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's right.\N{\rCHT}沒錯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.79,1:13:20.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's get this war started!\N{\rCHT}來開戰吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.09,1:13:50.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,So far all clear, Cap.\N{\rCHT}隊長 目前都安全{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.18,1:14:30.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\N{\rCHT}嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.67,1:14:32.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.38,1:15:27.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus, we didn't get all of them.\N{\rCHT}要命 還有活口{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.14,1:15:50.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退 撤退
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.61,1:15:53.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我們前進
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.03,1:15:56.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟我來
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.04,1:16:05.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Captain! What's the order?\N{\rCHT}隊長 你的命令呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.10,1:16:08.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cover Dostum! Follow him! Move!\N{\rCHT}掩護杜斯塔姆 跟上去 走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.07,1:16:11.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Move!\N{\rCHT}上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.26,1:16:23.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Milo!\N{\rCHT}米洛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.69,1:16:24.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ready?\N{\rCHT}準備好了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.31,1:16:30.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go!\N{\rCHT}上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.51,1:16:36.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Milo!\N{\rCHT}米洛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.86,1:16:39.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get the fuck over here!\N{\rCHT}快過來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.34,1:16:50.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.57,1:17:24.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jones!\N{\rCHT}鐘斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.79,1:17:25.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Huh?\N{\rCHT}啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.70,1:17:26.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Moving!\N{\rCHT}我要移動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.74,1:17:56.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rocket!\N{\rCHT}發射火箭彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.02,1:18:15.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,595, we're all clear.\N{\rCHT}595小隊 都安全了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.63,1:18:29.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第10天 解放後的貝沙姆村
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.48,1:18:37.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Try it again, bro.\N{\rCHT}再說一遍看看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.21,1:18:40.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,- "Motherfucker." - Mudda fuggah.\N{\rCHT}- 你媽的 - 你馬了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.43,1:18:43.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now we're getting somewhere.\N{\rCHT}有進步了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.91,1:18:51.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, I was thinking, uh,\N{\rCHT}我剛才在想{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.13,1:18:56.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,if I continue to follow you, I'm probably not gonna live very long.\N{\rCHT}再繼續跟著你 我八成活不久{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.76,1:18:59.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's some ballsy shit you did back there.\N{\rCHT}你剛才那樣沖 真是大膽{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.04,1:19:03.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you have to lead your men\N{\rCHT}有時你得帶領手下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.30,1:19:05.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,back into the right direction.\N{\rCHT}回到正軌{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.87,1:19:11.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's the game they're playing?\N{\rCHT}他們在玩什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.91,1:19:14.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Besh Tosh. Uzbek game.\N{\rCHT}"貝什托什" 烏茲別克遊戲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.50,1:19:15.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Besh Tosh?\N{\rCHT}"貝什托什"{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.73,1:19:17.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Besh, five.\N{\rCHT}"貝許"是5{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.84,1:19:19.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tosh, rocks.\N{\rCHT}"托許"是石頭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.20,1:19:24.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, when I ruled over Bescham,\N{\rCHT}在我掌管貝沙姆時{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.56,1:19:27.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,women wore no veils.\N{\rCHT}女人不戴面紗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.97,1:19:29.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Girls went to school.\N{\rCHT}女孩可以上學{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.60,1:19:33.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,We had movies at the theater.\N{\rCHT}劇院還會放電影{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.20,1:19:40.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,But here, Razzan killed my family.\N{\rCHT}但拉贊在這裡殺了我的家人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.30,1:19:46.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,I dreamed about taking it back, but now that I'm here,\N{\rCHT}我夢想將這裡收復 但現在來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.84,1:19:49.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna walk in.\N{\rCHT}我卻不想走進去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.59,1:19:53.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Too much pain.\N{\rCHT}太痛苦了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.51,1:20:00.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,I hope you never know it.\N{\rCHT}但願你永遠不用體會{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.79,1:20:03.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Uh, Cap?\N{\rCHT}隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.29,1:20:05.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\N{\rCHT}什麼事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.81,1:20:08.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,You got a message through secure interface with Bowers.\N{\rCHT}跟鮑爾斯的安全網路有你的信{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.34,1:20:09.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's from SecDef.\N{\rCHT}國防部長寄的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.46,1:20:11.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll read it later, man.\N{\rCHT}好 我待會再看{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.36,1:20:12.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Cap.\N{\rCHT}隊長 抱歉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.07,1:20:16.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Donald Rumsfeld just sent you an email and it aingt a good one.\N{\rCHT}拉姆斯菲爾德本人寫信給你 內容不妙{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.41,1:20:24.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's it say?\N{\rCHT}他寫什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.68,1:20:27.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,"When are you gonna get off your ass and get to Mazar?"\N{\rCHT}"你什麼時候才要滾去馬紮裡"{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.34,1:20:33.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.\N{\rCHT}真是的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.88,1:20:44.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know what? Write this back to him.\N{\rCHT}幫我回信給他{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.16,1:20:48.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Sir, let me explain the reality on the ground."\N{\rCHT}長官 容我說明戰地的實際狀況{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.79,1:20:51.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Write it.\N{\rCHT}寫啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.78,1:20:53.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.77,1:20:58.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,"I'm advising a man how to employ horse-mounted cavalry\N{\rCHT}我在協助一個人 騎馬打仗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.84,1:21:00.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,"against T-72 tanks,\N{\rCHT}對抗T-72坦克{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.17,1:21:03.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,mortars, machine guns."\N{\rCHT}迫擊炮 機關槍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.85,1:21:06.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,"A tactic I think became outdated\N{\rCHT}我原以為機槍發明後{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.17,1:21:08.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,"with the invention of the Gatling gun.\N{\rCHT}這戰術就已過時{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.82,1:21:12.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,"They've attacked with 10 rounds of AK-47 ammunition per man."\N{\rCHT}他們每個人的AK47 只有10發子彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.81,1:21:13.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lisa, get in here.\N{\rCHT}麗莎 快來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.97,1:21:16.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,"With snipers having less than 100 rounds\N{\rCHT}狙擊手的彈藥不到100發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.56,1:21:17.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,"with little water\N{\rCHT}水很少{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.28,1:21:19.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,and less food."\N{\rCHT}食物更少{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.17,1:21:22.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,The letter's too well written. I know it can't be Hal.\N{\rCHT}這文筆太好 不會是哈爾寫的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.94,1:21:24.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,"We witnessed the horse cavalry bounding\N{\rCHT}我們目睹這些騎兵{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.84,1:21:27.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,"from spur to spur to attack Taliban strongpoints.\N{\rCHT}翻山越嶺 攻打塔利班據點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.64,1:21:31.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,"The last several kilometers under mortar, artillery and sniper fire."\N{\rCHT}最後幾裡路 是頂著槍林炮雨{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.13,1:21:32.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's Mitch.\N{\rCHT}是米奇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.07,1:21:36.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Everywhere I go to, the civilian and local soldiers are always willing\N{\rCHT}所到之處的百姓士兵 都不吝告訴我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.59,1:21:38.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,"to tell me that they're glad the USA has come,\N{\rCHT}他們很高興美國來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.03,1:21:41.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,"and they speak of their hopes for a better Afghanistan\N{\rCHT}並期待塔利班垮臺後{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.54,1:21:43.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,once the Taliban are gone."\N{\rCHT}阿富汗會變好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.21,1:21:47.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第16天 C組 天吉峽谷北脊
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.30,1:22:05.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Raven, this is Charlie 595.\N{\rCHT}595小隊C組呼叫渡鴉{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.92,1:22:07.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good drop. Good drop.\N{\rCHT}仍得准 仍得准{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.73,1:22:10.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,We hit one of their outposts. Weapons cache destroyed.\N{\rCHT}擊中一支警戒部隊 及大量武器{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.35,1:22:12.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stand by for detailed sitrep to follow.\N{\rCHT}請待命 隨後有詳細報告{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.83,1:22:24.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,A組 峽谷南方 舒加雷山洞
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.54,1:22:28.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you take your grenade and throw it?\N{\rCHT}所以你就把手榴彈扔出去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.04,1:22:32.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,This should hold you for a while.\N{\rCHT}這樣應該可以撐一陣子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.78,1:22:35.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hey, get Mitch over here.\N{\rCHT}好 把米奇叫過來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.43,1:22:36.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, Captain!\N{\rCHT}隊長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.72,1:22:38.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. - Come over here, please!\N{\rCHT}- 什麼事 - 麻煩來一下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.95,1:22:41.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You all right? - Yeah, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你可以嗎 - 可以{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.86,1:22:46.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's like a javelin.\N{\rCHT}像擲標槍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.77,1:22:48.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You all right, Hal? - Oh, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 還好嗎 - 還好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.02,1:22:54.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you think you're making any progress with Dostum?\N{\rCHT}你跟杜斯塔姆有進展嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.68,1:22:56.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah, we're doing good.\N{\rCHT}有啊 我們挺好的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.71,1:22:59.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're thinking of getting an apartment together when this is all over.\N{\rCHT}正在考慮事後一起找房子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.04,1:23:01.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit.\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.63,1:23:03.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, don't make me laugh.\N{\rCHT}不要逗我笑{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.95,1:23:05.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Glad you got a sense of humor.\N{\rCHT}有幽默感是好事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.85,1:23:07.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I got some bad news. - What?\N{\rCHT}- 我有壞消息 - 什麼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.73,1:23:10.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Headquarters inserted ODA\N{\rCHT}總部把555小隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.60,1:23:13.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,555 with Atta's militia.\N{\rCHT}安插到阿塔那裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.11,1:23:15.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wait, General Atta, Dostum's rival?\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆的對頭阿塔將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.78,1:23:19.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,They think they have a better shot of reaching Mazar-i-Sharif.\N{\rCHT}他們覺得阿塔 比較有機會挺進馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.94,1:23:22.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't trust us to get through the gauntlet.\N{\rCHT}他們不信任我們能搞定{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.39,1:23:23.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,This kills us, Hal.\N{\rCHT}這樣會完蛋{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.64,1:23:25.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,The minute Dostum hears about Atta,\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆一聽說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.54,1:23:27.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,he's gonna forget all about the Taliban.\N{\rCHT}就不會管塔利班了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.90,1:23:28.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Could be.\N{\rCHT}有可能{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.97,1:23:31.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,You might wanna break up camp now,\N{\rCHT}最好現在拔營{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.76,1:23:33.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,in case you gotta get out of here quick.\N{\rCHT}以免馬上就要出發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.91,1:23:36.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, think of it this way.\N{\rCHT}這麼想吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.26,1:23:39.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've just been handed the most\N{\rCHT}你剛接下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.10,1:23:42.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,important diplomatic job in the free world.\N{\rCHT}自由世界的頭號外交工作{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.13,1:23:46.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keeping the Northern Alliance together.\N{\rCHT}讓北方聯盟維持統一{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.00,1:23:58.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第18天 C組 天吉峽谷北脊
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.97,1:24:14.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, finally. I'm starving to death.\N{\rCHT}總算啊 我要餓死了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.84,1:24:19.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Habib.\N{\rCHT}哈畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.68,1:24:23.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell him that I wanna buy one of his sheep.\N{\rCHT}跟他說我要買一頭羊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.36,1:24:30.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,He says they're not for sale.\N{\rCHT}他說是非賣品{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.30,1:24:32.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everything's for sale.\N{\rCHT}什麼東西都能賣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.60,1:24:35.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, tell him that we'll give him 50 American dollars.\N{\rCHT}跟他說我們付他50美元{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.71,1:24:44.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,He says he will take $500.\N{\rCHT}他要500美元{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.34,1:24:46.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,For that?\N{\rCHT}就一頭羊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.06,1:24:48.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,How much are they worth?\N{\rCHT}一頭值多少錢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.37,1:24:50.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- $100. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 100 - 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.96,1:24:57.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,300 American dollars.\N{\rCHT}300美元{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.49,1:24:59.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes?\N{\rCHT}好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.45,1:25:01.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good?\N{\rCHT}可以嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.92,1:25:04.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,This guy should be a fucking military contractor.\N{\rCHT}這傢伙應該去承包軍事業務{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.37,1:25:06.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- All right. - Great. Lamb chops.\N{\rCHT}- 好 - 太好了 羊小排{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.66,1:25:20.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a great day, my friend.\N{\rCHT}朋友 今天是好日子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.53,1:25:22.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Taliban pulled back to protect the Gap.\N{\rCHT}塔利班往後撤去守峽谷了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.80,1:25:26.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,We can move forward to here in the morning.\N{\rCHT}我們早上 就可以前進到這裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.87,1:25:29.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we do tomorrow right, we can run them all the way to Mazar.\N{\rCHT}要是明天用對兵 就能直沖馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.18,1:25:31.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,This war is won or lost tomorrow.\N{\rCHT}勝負就看明天{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.90,1:25:36.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,General,\N{\rCHT}將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.02,1:25:38.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wanna explain one of the other missions that are taking place tomorrow.\N{\rCHT}明天有另一個任務在執行{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.07,1:25:41.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's another team like mine,\N{\rCHT}另一支 我們這種小隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.10,1:25:43.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,and they've been placed with General Atta Mohammed.\N{\rCHT}被派給阿塔·穆罕默德將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.56,1:25:45.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're moving on Mazar from the southeast.\N{\rCHT}他們要從東南方 前往馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.68,1:25:47.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,They gave north to Atta.\N{\rCHT}他們把北部給了阿塔{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.15,1:25:49.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,From the U.S. point of view, you're all the Northern Alliance.\N{\rCHT}對美國來說 你們都是北方聯盟{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.55,1:25:52.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who is the U.S. to tell me what Northern Alliance is?\N{\rCHT}美國憑什麼 跟我指點北聯江山{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.33,1:25:54.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- If Atta moves to Mazar-i-Sharif first... - We're not dropping bombs\N{\rCHT}- 要是阿塔先到馬紮裡 - 我們投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.86,1:25:56.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,so you can go to war with Atta over the north.\N{\rCHT}不是為了讓你爭奪北部{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.60,1:25:58.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,The mission hasn't changed, General.\N{\rCHT}任務還是沒變{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.28,1:25:59.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're gonna punch through this Gap into the city.\N{\rCHT}我們將從峽谷挺進馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.91,1:26:02.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tiangi Gap is over two kilometers long.\N{\rCHT}天吉峽谷有2公里長{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.18,1:26:04.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Razzan's best weapons are right here.\N{\rCHT}拉贊最好的武器都在這裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.59,1:26:07.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Machine guns, mortars, heavy armors.\N{\rCHT}機關槍 迫擊炮 重型坦克{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.28,1:26:09.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,And right here is 055 Brigade.\N{\rCHT}這裡部署了055旅{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.00,1:26:12.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Foreign fighters. Al-Qaeda.They won't give an inch.\N{\rCHT}外籍戰士 基地組織 他們絕不會讓步{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.94,1:26:14.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,They prefer death.\N{\rCHT}他們寧可一死{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.48,1:26:17.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I won't let my men die so Atta can go to Mazar first.\N{\rCHT}我才不犧牲手下 來把阿塔送進馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.08,1:26:19.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,This isn't just your war, General.\N{\rCHT}這不只是你的戰爭 將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.18,1:26:21.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,There are thousands of people dead in your country and mine.\N{\rCHT}貴國和我國 都死了成千上萬人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.41,1:26:25.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now let me show you how this is possible. All right?\N{\rCHT}讓我說明為什麼可行 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.34,1:26:27.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,We've already lured them into this Gap.\N{\rCHT}我們已經把他們引進峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.86,1:26:29.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna put a man on each flank,\N{\rCHT}我會在兩側部署人手{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.78,1:26:32.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we're gonna overwhelm this canyon with air support.\N{\rCHT}用空援壓制整個峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.34,1:26:34.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've already sent Diller downrange.\N{\rCHT}我已經派迪勒到前方{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.01,1:26:36.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's gonna cut off any resupply and hit any retreat.\N{\rCHT}他會阻斷再補給 進行追擊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.70,1:26:38.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then, you and I are gonna charge through this Gap\N{\rCHT}你和我就沖過峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.99,1:26:41.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,and hit that main body with a full frontal assault.\N{\rCHT}正面攻擊他們的主要部隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.56,1:26:45.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,But Atta cannot get to Mazar first.\N{\rCHT}但不能讓阿塔先到馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.57,1:26:50.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm taking my men through there, General, with or without you.\N{\rCHT}你來或不來 我們都會執行到底{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.03,1:26:52.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Without me and my men, you are just an army of 12.\N{\rCHT}沒有我的部隊 你們只有12人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.86,1:26:55.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,You all will die. Good luck.\N{\rCHT}你們全都會死 祝好運{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.08,1:26:57.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,God damn it! You're unbelievable.\N{\rCHT}可惡 你真是太扯了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.95,1:27:01.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,You showed me the town where your family died.\N{\rCHT}你帶我 到你家人死去的城鎮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.40,1:27:05.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Told me every hell Razzan and his army unleashed on this place.\N{\rCHT}讓我看到 拉贊陣營製造的煉獄{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.21,1:27:08.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,And now all you care about is some turf war?\N{\rCHT}結果你就只在乎搶地盤{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.62,1:27:12.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,You lectured me about the heart of a warrior.\N{\rCHT}你叫我 要擁有戰士的心{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.00,1:27:15.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're no warrior. You're just another warlord.\N{\rCHT}你才不是戰士 只是另一個軍閥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.90,1:27:18.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, go ahead.\N{\rCHT}你走啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.13,1:27:20.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,It aingt us that's quitting, General, it's you.\N{\rCHT}放棄的不是我們 是你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.07,1:27:35.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not a happy face.\N{\rCHT}臉色很不好喔{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.23,1:27:39.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't think Dostum's on board.\N{\rCHT}我覺得杜斯塔姆不幹了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.10,1:27:42.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you mean not on board?\N{\rCHT}什麼叫不幹了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.58,1:27:43.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,He says he's not gonna fight a\N{\rCHT}他說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.77,1:27:46.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,battle that opens a way for his rival to take the city.\N{\rCHT}不替死對頭開路拿下馬紮裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.20,1:27:47.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not very big-picture of him.\N{\rCHT}他這樣格局有點小{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.08,1:27:50.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's fighting more than one war here.\N{\rCHT}他的對手不只一個{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.79,1:27:53.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't like it, but these are the cards we've been dealt.\N{\rCHT}我也不樂意 但現實如此{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.24,1:27:55.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, well, Captain, you gotta talk to him. - I did.\N{\rCHT}- 隊長 你得找他談 - 談過了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.86,1:27:56.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's gone.\N{\rCHT}他已經走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.63,1:28:00.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's taken most of his men, most of the militia, and they left.\N{\rCHT}帶著大部分手下和民兵走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.28,1:28:05.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, I aingt gonna lie to you guys.\N{\rCHT}我就不騙你們了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.03,1:28:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,The chances are we are not gonna make it out of this one.\N{\rCHT}我們八成無法全身而退{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.22,1:28:14.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Goddamn, we're this close.\N{\rCHT}可惡 就差這一小步{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.35,1:28:18.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're so close to wiping Al-Qaeda out of Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}再一步 就能把基地組織徹底趕走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.10,1:28:21.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll never get another chance like this.\N{\rCHT}這種機會不會再有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.35,1:28:23.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,But if we quit now,\N{\rCHT}要是現在放棄{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.65,1:28:27.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,then what happened back home is gonna happen again\N{\rCHT}世貿的事就會一而再{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.27,1:28:29.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,and again.\N{\rCHT}再而三發生{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.62,1:28:33.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Each of you gotta make this decision,\N{\rCHT}你們都必須做出決定{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.82,1:28:35.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,but I'm in.\N{\rCHT}但我會上陣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.21,1:28:39.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're ready for anything.\N{\rCHT}我們早就做好準備{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.74,1:28:41.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,With or without him.\N{\rCHT}不管他參不參與{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.53,1:28:44.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fuck him.\N{\rCHT}去他的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.44,1:28:46.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean, we're already here, right?\N{\rCHT}來都來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.65,1:28:48.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.\N{\rCHT}那好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.30,1:28:50.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,We go in the morning.\N{\rCHT}我們早上出發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.83,1:28:52.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,You take what's left of the guards with you.\N{\rCHT}把剩下的衛兵都帶上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.95,1:28:54.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,And get some rest tonight.\N{\rCHT}今晚好好休息{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.64,1:28:56.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's gonna decide it one way or another.\N{\rCHT}勝負就看明天了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.86,1:29:01.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Spencer, Black.\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞 布萊克{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.51,1:29:03.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,You call in airstrikes from the eastern flank.\N{\rCHT}從東側請求空襲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.49,1:29:08.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Milo, Jackson and Essex have been pushed out\N{\rCHT}米洛 傑克遜 艾塞克斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.74,1:29:11.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,against the enemy's western flank right here.\N{\rCHT}被派到西翼這裡 逼進敵人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.97,1:29:13.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Diller, Coffers and Bennett\N{\rCHT}迪勒 考佛和貝內特{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.54,1:29:15.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,will cover the enemy's northern flank\N{\rCHT}會守住敵軍北側{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.00,1:29:17.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,in an attempt to block reinforcements from Mazar.\N{\rCHT}阻擋來自馬紮裡的增援{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.58,1:29:20.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Falls and Michaels, cover Jones and me\N{\rCHT}法爾斯和麥克斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.96,1:29:23.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,from the sniper position on the southern flank.\N{\rCHT}從南邊的狙擊點 掩護鐘斯和我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.29,1:29:25.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,抵達第20天 天吉峽谷 南側
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.96,1:29:28.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here we go down the rabbit hole.\N{\rCHT}要迎向未知了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.75,1:29:35.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,- All right, Vern. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 克斯 - 怎麼樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.66,1:29:36.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who wins in a fight?\N{\rCHT}打架誰會贏{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.68,1:29:39.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Queen Elizabeth or Margaret Thatcher?\N{\rCHT}英國女王還是柴契爾夫人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.20,1:29:42.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jesus, Falls. Where do you come up with this shit?\N{\rCHT}靠 這是哪來的鳥問題{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.53,1:29:44.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,From the depths of my brilliant mind.\N{\rCHT}我聰明過人的腦袋想的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.63,1:29:48.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Seeing that, boss?\N{\rCHT}老大 看到了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.45,1:29:55.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Falls, a scout just picked us up.\N{\rCHT}法爾斯 有偵察兵發現我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.46,1:29:56.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,My two o'clock. Over.\N{\rCHT}在我2點鐘方向 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.22,1:29:58.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Target.\N{\rCHT}出現目標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.00,1:30:00.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Got him.\N{\rCHT}發現了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.78,1:30:04.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,650 yards.\N{\rCHT}650碼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.14,1:30:07.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hold to left.\N{\rCHT}向左修正{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.85,1:30:13.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good hit.\N{\rCHT}漂亮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.56,1:30:23.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,C組 天吉峽谷 北側
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.62,1:30:30.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Coffers, get that radio up.\N{\rCHT}考佛 架設無線電{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.70,1:30:32.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need 10 minutes.\N{\rCHT}要10分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.38,1:30:33.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,You got five.\N{\rCHT}給你5分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.48,1:30:36.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like I said, five minutes.\N{\rCHT}我說了啊 5分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.00,1:30:55.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,No Dostum, huh?\N{\rCHT}沒看到杜斯塔姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.13,1:31:02.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,K2 base, this is 595 Delta. Over.\N{\rCHT}595小隊D組呼叫K2 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.87,1:31:06.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Request medevac on standby. Over.\N{\rCHT}請求救護直升機待命 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.94,1:31:07.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Roger.\N{\rCHT}收到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.86,1:31:11.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Shit. - How we looking, J?\N{\rCHT}- 媽的 - 情況如何{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.80,1:31:13.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eh. We're in the right spot.\N{\rCHT}我們來對地方了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.05,1:31:17.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fuck, there's gotta be at least 15,000 down there.\N{\rCHT}靠 底下起碼1萬5兵力{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.95,1:31:19.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,B組 天吉峽谷 東側
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.40,1:31:20.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Spencer, this is Alpha. We're in position.\N{\rCHT}A組呼叫斯賓塞{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.61,1:31:22.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Start lasing targets of opportunity.\N{\rCHT}A組就位 開始尋找臨時目標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.47,1:31:24.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Biggest guns first. Over.\N{\rCHT}先攻擊最大火力 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.09,1:31:25.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am your biggest gun, Cap.\N{\rCHT}我就是你的最大火力{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.85,1:31:28.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Diller, welcome back, man. How was your trip?\N{\rCHT}迪勒 歡迎歸隊 旅途如何{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.32,1:31:29.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm doing great.\N{\rCHT}非常好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.50,1:31:31.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm looking at timeshares over here for the summer.\N{\rCHT}我正在物色夏天專用的別墅{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.65,1:31:34.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's do this, boys.\N{\rCHT}好 那就開始吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.48,1:31:36.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heads down, stay safe.\N{\rCHT}千萬小心 一切平安{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.10,1:31:37.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, good to go.\N{\rCHT}我們準備好了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.45,1:31:43.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, yo, J? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 嘿 你 老傑 - 怎麼樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.92,1:31:46.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,055 brigade. Al-Qaeda.\N{\rCHT}055旅 基地組織{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.34,1:31:49.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gotta lead them a bit more, bro.\N{\rCHT}得再把他們引出來一點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.92,1:31:51.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Gotcha.\N{\rCHT}好 知道了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.24,1:31:55.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Viper 47, this is Bravo 595.\N{\rCHT}595小隊B組 呼叫毒蛇47{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.71,1:31:57.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Laser target designator\N{\rCHT}鐳射目標指示{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.64,1:32:04.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Target, tanks in the open.\N{\rCHT}目標是 空曠處的坦克車{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.06,1:32:40.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nice shot, chief.\N{\rCHT}准喔 大哥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.92,1:32:44.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,How's that taste, huh?\N{\rCHT}滋味如何啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.59,1:32:47.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, Bravo, good drop. Shift your targets\N{\rCHT}B組 炸得好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.52,1:32:49.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,500 meters south. Over.\N{\rCHT}目標往南移5百公尺 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.08,1:32:52.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Viper 47, new target.\N{\rCHT}毒蛇47 新目標{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.68,1:32:56.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Multiple troops in the open. Drop 500 meters east of...\N{\rCHT}空曠處的裝甲部隊 往東邊5百公尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.45,1:32:59.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Chief? Chief, chief, chief.\N{\rCHT}大哥 大哥 大哥 大哥{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.92,1:33:01.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,How'd they find us?\N{\rCHT}他們怎麼找來的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.66,1:33:03.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,They surrendering?\N{\rCHT}他們要投降嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.60,1:33:10.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Chief, are they surrendering?\N{\rCHT}是投降嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.30,1:33:13.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maybe.\N{\rCHT}有可能{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.22,1:33:15.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Might be a trick.\N{\rCHT}也可能有詐{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.62,1:33:17.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep your finger on the trigger, okay?\N{\rCHT}隨時準備開火{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.73,1:33:19.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要輕舉妄動
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.71,1:33:20.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you wanna do with them?\N{\rCHT}要怎麼處置{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.43,1:33:28.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Alpha 595, this is Bravo 595.\N{\rCHT}595小隊B組呼叫A組{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.38,1:33:29.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,We got a situation here.\N{\rCHT}這裡有狀況{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.83,1:33:34.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Multiple enemy combatants attempting to surrender at our position.\N{\rCHT}多名敵方戰鬥員 前來意圖投降{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.21,1:33:36.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,手舉起來
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.83,1:33:40.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Roger, Bravo. Give me a sitrep when they're contained. Over.\N{\rCHT}收到 把他們控制住就報告 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.25,1:33:51.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Flash 21, this is 595 Charlie.\N{\rCHT}595小隊C組呼叫閃光21{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.19,1:33:52.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Request immediate...\N{\rCHT}請求即刻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.11,1:34:07.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,We gotta get that goddamn antenna!\N{\rCHT}得把天線撿回來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.12,1:34:09.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cover me!\N{\rCHT}掩護我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.08,1:34:30.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit!\N{\rCHT}靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.20,1:34:34.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,They got a BM-21 and they're going into the Gap!\N{\rCHT}有多管火箭炮開進峽谷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.50,1:34:40.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you want to surrender?\N{\rCHT}你們要投降嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.67,1:34:42.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?\N{\rCHT}聽得懂嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.05,1:34:45.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no. Just stay there.\N{\rCHT}不要 留在原地{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.85,1:34:49.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stay there, okay?\N{\rCHT}別過來 好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.49,1:34:53.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you wish to surrender, you stay right there.\N{\rCHT}如果要投降 就別再靠近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.73,1:34:54.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stop.\N{\rCHT}站住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.11,1:34:56.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.\N{\rCHT}好嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.10,1:35:09.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. We gotta search each one of these guys.\N{\rCHT}好 所有人都得搜身{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.81,1:35:10.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,One by one.\N{\rCHT}一個一個搜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.48,1:35:14.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You hear me? - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 聽到了嗎 - 好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.20,1:35:16.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stay sharp.\N{\rCHT}保持警覺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.03,1:36:03.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hal? Hal? Shit.\N{\rCHT}哈爾 哈爾 見鬼{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.53,1:36:05.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit! Hal? Hal?\N{\rCHT}可惡 哈爾 哈爾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.76,1:36:09.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hal? Oh, God.\N{\rCHT}哈爾 天哪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.86,1:36:12.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hal, come on, buddy. Hal. Hal!\N{\rCHT}醒醒啊兄弟 哈爾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.68,1:36:15.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shit.\N{\rCHT}媽的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.89,1:36:20.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. Hal. Hal, come on, buddy. Come on.\N{\rCHT}不要啊 哈爾 你撐住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.75,1:36:22.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\N{\rCHT}不 不 不{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.53,1:36:26.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hal! Come on! Oh, shit!\N{\rCHT}哈爾 撐住啊 可惡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.35,1:36:30.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy. Come on.\N{\rCHT}兄弟 撐住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.06,1:36:34.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Any station, Bravo is down! Bravo is down!\N{\rCHT}呼叫各組 B組有人受傷{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.48,1:36:36.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,How bad?\N{\rCHT}多嚴重{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.74,1:36:39.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bad! I need immediate medevac!\N{\rCHT}很嚴重 必須即刻送離{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.83,1:36:40.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm on it, sir.\N{\rCHT}我馬上聯絡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.70,1:36:52.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, fix this!\N{\rCHT}把線接好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.25,1:37:04.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sir, better late than never, huh?\N{\rCHT}隊長 遲到總比不到好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.41,1:37:28.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's go! Let's go!\N{\rCHT}快快快{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.42,1:37:30.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How about now? - Yeah, yeah. Good, good.\N{\rCHT}- 行了嗎 - 行了 通了通了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.13,1:37:33.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Alpha, this is Charlie. Do you read me?\N{\rCHT}C組呼叫A組 聽到了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.47,1:37:34.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\N{\rCHT}你說{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.46,1:37:37.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's a BM-21 in the Gap, loaded with rockets.\N{\rCHT}穀內有裝填完畢的多管火箭炮{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.17,1:37:38.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit.\N{\rCHT}可惡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.23,1:37:59.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,What the fuck is that?\N{\rCHT}那是怎麼回事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.32,1:38:38.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Black, give me Spencer's status.\N{\rCHT}布萊克 報告斯賓塞的狀況{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.17,1:38:40.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a sucking chest wound. He's on a real clock here.\N{\rCHT}是開放性氣胸傷口 他時間不多{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.09,1:38:45.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, ready? Three, two, one. Up. Let's go. Easy.\N{\rCHT}預備 3 2 1 抬 小心{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.67,1:38:46.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey. Movement.\N{\rCHT}喂 有動靜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.38,1:38:50.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Let's roll, boys. Let's roll. - Get down. Get down. Get down. Get down.\N{\rCHT}- 趕快攻擊 - 趴下 趴下 趴下 趴下{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.80,1:39:20.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Essex, can you target the BM-21?\N{\rCHT}艾塞克斯 你能鎖定火箭炮嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.13,1:39:23.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Negative.\N{\rCHT}沒辦法{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.87,1:39:26.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pulling back?\N{\rCHT}要撤退嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.14,1:39:28.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Back to the horses. Move!\N{\rCHT}撤退去騎馬 走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.51,1:39:32.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go!\N{\rCHT}快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.22,1:39:45.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Taliban's gonna swamp your position before a medevac can get in.\N{\rCHT}塔利班會比救護機先到你們那裡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.86,1:39:47.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put the radio to Spencer's ear.\N{\rCHT}讓斯賓塞聽{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.59,1:39:54.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, this is double or nothing, Hal.\N{\rCHT}現在不是一舉兩得 就是完敗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.30,1:39:55.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're gonna evac you.\N{\rCHT}我們要把你送走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.49,1:39:57.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't stop.\N{\rCHT}不要停{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.40,1:39:59.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're not.\N{\rCHT}不會的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.32,1:40:01.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're gonna airlift you from the other side of the Gap\N{\rCHT}我們要在峽谷的另一頭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.00,1:40:02.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,on the road to Mazar-i-Sharif.\N{\rCHT}把你送走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.76,1:40:04.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the only way, Hal.\N{\rCHT}只有這個辦法了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.22,1:40:06.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember, the only way home is winning.\N{\rCHT}記住 想回家就只能贏{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.72,1:40:08.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,You hang in there, my friend.\N{\rCHT}你要撐住 朋友{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.28,1:40:32.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Call the drop now!\N{\rCHT}快請求投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.91,1:40:37.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,464, adjust your target 20 meters west.\N{\rCHT}464 目標往西調整20公尺{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.23,1:40:38.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,How copy? Over.\N{\rCHT}收到了嗎 完畢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.46,1:40:41.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good copy, 595. But we are not authorized so close to you.\N{\rCHT}一清二楚 但距離太近 超出許可權{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.32,1:40:44.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Danger close, bro!\N{\rCHT}射程內投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.59,1:40:48.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,464, requesting danger close ordnance!\N{\rCHT}464 請求射程內投彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.70,1:40:50.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Copy that. Danger close. Twenty seconds.\N{\rCHT}收到 射程內投彈 20秒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.94,1:41:01.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Get the fuck out of here! - Let's go! Let's go! Run! Run!\N{\rCHT}- 快走 - 快走 快跑{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.83,1:41:36.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Essex?\N{\rCHT}艾塞克斯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.59,1:41:40.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jackson?\N{\rCHT}傑克遜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.05,1:41:41.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}嗯{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.40,1:41:49.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Najeeb?\N{\rCHT}納吉布{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.76,1:41:54.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Najeeb.\N{\rCHT}納吉布{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.65,1:41:56.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Najeeb.\N{\rCHT}納吉布{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.54,1:42:06.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, Najeeb. Come on.\N{\rCHT}挺住 納吉布 挺住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.47,1:42:07.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Milo?\N{\rCHT}米洛{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.82,1:42:09.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,E!\N{\rCHT}老艾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.78,1:42:17.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, Najeeb. Come on, bro. Come on. Come on.\N{\rCHT}起來啊 納吉布 快起來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.60,1:42:25.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Are you okay? - Go help Jackson.\N{\rCHT}- 你還好嗎 - 去扶傑克遜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.04,1:42:26.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Okay? Look at me! - Go help Jackson!\N{\rCHT}- 好嗎 你看著我 - 去扶傑克遜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.74,1:42:27.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Help Jackson!\N{\rCHT}去扶傑克遜啦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.60,1:42:30.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jackson?\N{\rCHT}傑克遜{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.50,1:42:32.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get up!\N{\rCHT}起來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.48,1:42:34.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Get up! - Come on.\N{\rCHT}- 起來 - 來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.14,1:42:38.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,We gotta go. We gotta fucking go.\N{\rCHT}我們這就走 他媽的這就走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.83,1:42:41.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,E!\N{\rCHT}老艾{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.53,1:42:44.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. All right?\N{\rCHT}你可以嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.82,1:42:48.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Najeeb?\N{\rCHT}納吉布{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.99,1:42:53.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on. Let it out, man. Come on.\N{\rCHT}來 咳出來 來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.13,1:42:55.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let it out.\N{\rCHT}咳出來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.08,1:42:56.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,We gotta go. We gotta go.\N{\rCHT}我們得趕快走了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.84,1:43:13.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cap, we lost communication with Essex.\N{\rCHT}隊長 艾塞克斯斷訊了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.54,1:43:14.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep trying them.\N{\rCHT}繼續呼叫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.82,1:43:18.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, if we don't take out that BM-21,this whole thing is over.\N{\rCHT}聽著 不毀了火箭炮 就全盤皆輸了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.33,1:43:20.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,It fires 40 rockets in salvos. Got it?\N{\rCHT}它一次是40連發 懂嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.12,1:43:23.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forty, and then two minutes to reload. Say it back to me.\N{\rCHT}40連發 裝填要2分鐘 說一遍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.76,1:43:24.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Two minutes.\N{\rCHT}2分鐘{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.68,1:43:26.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's how long we're gonna have to storm their positions,\N{\rCHT}我們可以趁機猛攻{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.66,1:43:27.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,but we gotta get closer.\N{\rCHT}但必須先往前沖{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.80,1:43:29.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,And hold there until they stop to reload.\N{\rCHT}然後挺住 直到他們裝彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.65,1:43:32.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,K2 base, this is Alpha.\N{\rCHT}A組呼叫K2基地{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.72,1:43:35.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lead elements crossing phase line red.\N{\rCHT}主力部隊 將跨過最後調整線{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.43,1:43:37.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anticipate high casualties.\N{\rCHT}準備迎接大量傷亡{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.20,1:43:57.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,他要衝了 跟他走
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.03,1:46:22.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're gonna have to reload soon. We'll have two...\N{\rCHT}快要重新裝彈了 會有2分{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.15,1:47:11.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, shit!\N{\rCHT}我靠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.56,1:47:34.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Captain! - Now's our window. Let's go!\N{\rCHT}- 隊長 - 空檔來了 我們上{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.18,1:48:17.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Contact front!\N{\rCHT}正面敵軍炮襲{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.33,1:50:40.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where's Diller?\N{\rCHT}迪勒人呢{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.84,1:50:42.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Moving to our position.\N{\rCHT}正往我們這裡移動{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.73,1:50:44.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bird incoming in two minutes.\N{\rCHT}直升機2分鐘後到{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.16,1:50:49.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Copy. Rendezvous at evac sight and pop smoke.\N{\rCHT}收到 現場集合 放信號彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.34,1:51:46.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get the horses out of here! There's a chopper coming.\N{\rCHT}把馬牽走 直升機要來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.33,1:51:50.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How's he doing? - Cap, I need that medevac here right now!\N{\rCHT}- 他怎麼樣 - 隊長 得現在就送他走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.38,1:51:52.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- All right, it's coming. It's coming. - Chopper's inbound!\N{\rCHT}- 好 已經來了 - 直升機飛近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.25,1:51:53.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jones, get that smoke out!\N{\rCHT}鐘斯 放信號彈{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.00,1:51:55.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, here they come, buddy. Here they come.\N{\rCHT}兄弟 直升機來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.18,1:51:57.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,You hang in there, buddy.\N{\rCHT}你要撐住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.83,1:51:59.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did we get them?\N{\rCHT}搞定他們了嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.41,1:52:01.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, man. We got them. We got them good.\N{\rCHT}有 徹底搞定他們了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.06,1:52:06.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey, you hang in there. Don't you quit on us.\N{\rCHT}喂 你撐住 可別扔下我們{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.67,1:52:34.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's cover him up! Cover up!\N{\rCHT}把他蓋起來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.92,1:52:59.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, ready? Three, two, one! Up!\N{\rCHT}預備 3 2 1 抬{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.31,1:53:25.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Has anyone seen Dostum?\N{\rCHT}有人看見杜斯塔姆嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.87,1:53:28.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eye in the sky says full retreat over here.\N{\rCHT}空中觀測到敵軍全數撤退{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.28,1:53:29.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,The whole Gap is clear.\N{\rCHT}整個峽谷都淨空了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.53,1:53:31.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're bugging out all the way from Mazar.\N{\rCHT}他們從馬紮裡落荒而逃{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.48,1:53:34.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Does air visual have eyes on Atta's militia?\N{\rCHT}有觀測到阿塔的民兵嗎{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.43,1:53:36.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're approaching from the east.\N{\rCHT}有 他們從東邊靠近{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.59,1:53:38.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dostum's going for Atta.\N{\rCHT}杜斯塔姆去追阿塔了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.50,1:53:41.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,This whole thing falls apart if the Northern Alliance breaks.\N{\rCHT}要是北方聯盟分裂 大局就毀了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.73,1:53:43.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have to get to Dostum first!\N{\rCHT}我們得先追上杜斯塔姆{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.87,1:53:45.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Head to Mazar!\N{\rCHT}往馬紮裡出發{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.87,1:53:46.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's go!\N{\rCHT}快走{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.71,1:54:30.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬紮裡沙裡夫
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.90,1:54:41.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,General, wait.\N{\rCHT}將軍 等等{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.62,1:54:42.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,General Atta.\N{\rCHT}阿塔將軍{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.74,1:55:19.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,I will let Atta have the city today.\N{\rCHT}今天馬紮裡就讓給阿塔{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.69,1:55:21.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we'll see.\N{\rCHT}明天再等著瞧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.02,1:55:24.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, you made the right choice.\N{\rCHT}你做了正確的選擇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.08,1:55:27.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right choice?\N{\rCHT}正確的選擇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.31,1:55:30.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,There are no right choices here.\N{\rCHT}這裡沒那回事{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.48,1:55:31.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is Afghanistan.\N{\rCHT}這裡是阿富汗{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.48,1:55:35.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Graveyard of many empires.\N{\rCHT}許許多多帝國的墳場{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.35,1:55:39.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Today you are our friend, tomorrow you are our enemy.\N{\rCHT}今天是朋友 明天就是敵人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.92,1:55:43.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,It won't be any different for you.\N{\rCHT}就算是你們 也一樣{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.50,1:55:46.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Soon America will become just\N{\rCHT}美國將成為這裡的{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.34,1:55:48.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,another tribe here.\N{\rCHT}另一個族群{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.18,1:55:54.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,You will be cowards if you leave.\N{\rCHT}如果你們離開 就是懦夫{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.20,1:55:58.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you will be our enemies if you stay.\N{\rCHT}留下來 就是我們的敵人{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.30,1:56:03.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just know\N{\rCHT}只要記住{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.00,1:56:06.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,that you will always be my brother.\N{\rCHT}你永遠都是我的兄弟{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.58,1:56:10.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,When I get into that city,\N{\rCHT}等我進城{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.73,1:56:12.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I will raise your flag.\N{\rCHT}我會升起你的旗幟{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.74,1:56:15.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's your city, General. You raise your own flag.\N{\rCHT}你的城市 升你的旗幟就好{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.76,1:56:17.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here.\N{\rCHT}拿去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.96,1:56:20.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's been with me forever.\N{\rCHT}這短鞭跟了我一輩子{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.39,1:56:23.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Now it's yours. - Thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 送給你了 - 謝謝你{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.82,1:56:37.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yo.\N{\rCHT}喂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.48,1:56:41.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you for looking out for me.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你照顧我{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.77,1:56:49.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you cry, I'm telling everyone.\N{\rCHT}你要是哭了 我會告訴大家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.14,1:56:51.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shut the fuck up, bro.\N{\rCHT}你閉嘴啦{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.86,1:56:55.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!\N{\rCHT}歡迎歸隊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.29,1:57:07.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Changed the extraction site, huh?\N{\rCHT}你改了撤離地點{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.85,1:57:09.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I didn't think you'd walked far enough.\N{\rCHT}我覺得你走不了那麼遠{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.18,1:57:13.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I was thinking, you know what, my knees feel way too good.\N{\rCHT}是啊 我還想說我的膝蓋也太勇{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.79,1:57:15.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well, they look good. - Thanks.\N{\rCHT}- 看起來是很勇 - 謝了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.89,1:57:17.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Did you see the medic? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 給醫務官看過了嗎 - 有{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.85,1:57:24.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Feels good, huh?\N{\rCHT}感覺很棒吧{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.35,1:57:28.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,What, sitting down? Awesome.\N{\rCHT}坐下嗎 棒呆了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.56,1:57:31.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I mean to finally see one through.\N{\rCHT}我是說總算達成任務{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.37,1:57:35.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.40,1:57:37.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}很棒{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.89,1:57:39.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,We won the battle, you know.\N{\rCHT}我們贏了這場戰役{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.27,1:57:41.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Still gotta win the war.\N{\rCHT}但還得打贏戰爭{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.13,1:57:44.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That aingt up to us.\N{\rCHT}由不得我們決定{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.63,1:57:47.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Aingt our job anyway though, right?\N{\rCHT}那也不是我們的工作{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.85,1:57:48.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.43,1:57:52.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, where are you going to point us to next?\N{\rCHT}你接著要派我們去哪{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:53.87,1:57:55.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm pointing us home.\N{\rCHT}我要派你們回家{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.04,1:57:58.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you there.\N{\rCHT}我跟你去{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.63,1:58:01.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you anywhere.\N{\rCHT}我會追隨你到天涯海角{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.77,1:58:06.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank God for that.\N{\rCHT}謝天謝地{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.88,1:58:47.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,烏茲別克 K2基地 抵達第23天
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.31,1:59:19.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Spencer?\N{\rCHT}斯賓塞如何{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.21,1:59:22.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's stable. On his way to Germany.\N{\rCHT}傷勢穩定 正在送往德國{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.22,1:59:23.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,You got him here in time.\N{\rCHT}你及時把他送出來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.76,1:59:28.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Kept your promise.\N{\rCHT}你說到做到了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.52,1:59:29.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\N{\rCHT}是的 長官{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.70,1:59:49.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's beautiful, Maddy.\N{\rCHT}好漂亮喔 瑪蒂{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.15,2:00:02.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maddy! Come here!\N{\rCHT}瑪蒂 過來{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.96,2:00:06.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, Christmas came early!\N{\rCHT}你看 耶誕節提前來了{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.26,2:00:07.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Daddy!\N{\rCHT}爸爸{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.35,2:00:20.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,儘管困難重重 特戰隊595小隊12人 仍全數平安歸來
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.56,2:00:24.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,這支馬兵與友軍攻下馬紮裡沙裡夫 為美軍最驚人的成就之一
Dialogue: 0,2:00:24.77,2:00:29.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,軍事策劃家預料需耗時2年 刺刀特遣隊3周就達成任務
Dialogue: 0,2:00:29.07,2:00:34.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,此事被基地組織視為最大慘敗
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.25,2:00:40.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,由於是機密任務 595小隊的隊員們返家後回歸平凡
Dialogue: 0,2:00:40.69,2:00:43.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,未受到任何英雄式歡迎或公開致意
Dialogue: 0,2:00:43.96,2:00:48.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,2014年 杜斯塔姆將軍出任阿富汗副總統
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.84,2:00:52.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,他與米契尼爾森至今仍是摯友
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.76,2:00:58.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,2012年 為了向他們的英勇表現致敬
Dialogue: 0,2:00:58.20,2:01:02.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,民間團體捐贈了一座馬兵雕像 就樹立在世貿遺址前
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.03,2:01:14.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,特戰隊595小隊

